\id REV - Akawaio New Testament Translation Project 
\h ISENPOIKASA' 
\toc1 Isenpoikasa' Rʉ'pʉ Isaan Ena' 
\toc2 Isenpoikasa' 
\toc3 Isenpoikasa' 
\mt1 Isenpoikasa' Rʉ'pʉ 
\mt2 Isaan Ena' 
\imt1 Ekamanin 
\ip \bk Isenpoikasa' Rʉ'pʉ Isaan Ena' \bk* e'menuka'pʉ Kʉri'san amʉ' kota'ma a'tai, apʉne pʉra Sises Kʉrai apurɨ to' uya wenai Itepuru pe. Imenukanin e'ku'to' ipɨ' kuru esi'pʉ tʉnmenuka'pʉ ennin nan repato' pe tʉuya to' e'ku'to' ike ke, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' epori'mapɨ'to' ike ke, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsɨ moronkato' to' uya yau, tʉkota'mato' kon yau to' e'to' pe te'nonkai' pʉra. 
\ip Eke pe kuru kareta yau tu'ke kuru isenpoikasa' ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ en uta'kwakasa' nene'pʉ ton usekama ento' ipɨkɨron main yau, mɨrɨ a'taino kon Kʉri'san amʉ' nʉto'ka'nʉkʉnʉ pe, e'tane tʉron kon nʉto'ka'nʉkʉnʉ pe pʉra rɨ nin si iye'nonkasa'. Eren esi tese' ke'ne kasa, serɨ kareta yawo'nan itese' ton utakonomapɨtʉ ti'tui' pʉra tu'kan winɨ rɨ en uta'kwakasa' nene'san winɨ rɨ. Ɨsi'tai rɨ eseru wannɨ e'tane serɨ kareta yawon enpoikato' yai, itesa' ese' esi tensen pe kuru rɨ: Kʉrai, Itepuru poro, Papa uya tanporo teyaton non ma'tanʉ'to' oton ipʉra rɨ, Se'tan pokon pe rɨ, mɨrɨpan uya tʉmaimu awɨron kon tʉmunkɨ ton e'mato' oton emenna' Epʉn ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ emenna' non ke to' entai tena to' enuka'nʉ'sa' tʉuya a'tai. 
\iot Iyawon Ekamanin 
\io1 Ekamanin (1:1-8) 
\io1 En uta'kwaka, uta'koka, enno'pɨ'sa' kareta 7 pan so'si ena' (1:9—3:22) 
\io1 Kareta amon 7 kaisaron a'si'to' esa' (4:1—8:1) 
\io1 7 kaisaron wai, tʉronpi' itese' (8:2—11:19) 
\io1 Urupere mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asa'ron kon ene amʉ' (12:1—13:18) 
\io1 Ɨsi'taino en uta'kwakasa' nene'pʉ (14:1—15:8) 
\io1 7 kaisaron pʉsau Papa sakorooi euku yen ton (16:1-21) 
\io1 Paperan uma'ta, Ene wɨnɨ, ennakanin pu'kena', Makoi (17:1—20:10) 
\io1 Iu'matʉ a'taino eseru aimenkato' (20:11-15) 
\io1 Emenna' Epʉn, emenna' non, emenna' Surusiran (21:1—22:5) 
\io1 Iu'ma'sa' (22:6-21) 
\c 1  
\s1 Ekamanin 
\p  
\v 1 Serɨ kareta esi Sises Kʉrai nenpoika'pʉ, Papa nʉtʉrʉ'pʉ itena', tʉpoitorʉ ton auro'kato' pe iya serɨ pe'ne kuru te'ku'sen pɨ'. Kʉrai uya serɨ ton enpoika'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ Isaan ena', tinserʉʉi tenno'se ipiya'.  
\v 2 Tanporo Isaan uya tʉnene'pʉ menukasa', serɨ si inmenuka'pʉ Papa maimu mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'napairon Sises Kʉrai nenpoika'pʉ.  
\v 3 Pori' pe kuru kʉrɨ rɨ imenu ennin pe na'ne' esi mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro nɨrɨ serɨ te'ku'ton ekamanin main etanin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ anʉnnin nan serɨ kareta yau iye'menukasa' na'ne', apʉne pʉra a'ko pe iye'ku'to' weyu esi pɨ'. 
\s1 Miyarɨ Tato' 7 Kaisaron So'si Pɨ' 
\p  
\v 4 Isaan winɨpaino, 7 kaisaron so'si amʉ' Eisa po te'san enakan. Wakʉ nonkasa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' nesii ɨpiyau'nokon, moro te'sen, moro iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuye'ton winɨpaino, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisaron kon iya'kwarʉ amʉ'\f + \fr 1:4 \fq 7 kaisaron kon iya'kwarʉ amʉ'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq 7 pe iku'nin a'kwarʉ.\f* iyapon rau te'san winɨpaino,\x - \xo 1:4 \xt E'sotas 3:14; Isenpoikasa' 4:5\x* 
\v 5 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Sises Kʉrai winɨpaino, i'napai rɨ kuru ekamanin, wapiya kuru iyentusa' rʉ'pʉ e'mʉ'sa'kasa' rʉ'pʉ eri'nɨto' yapai, mɨrɨpan esi non pon kon kin amʉ' epuru pe. 
\p Tɨwɨ ui'nʉnkanin kon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ umo'kanin kon umakooi kon yapai tʉmʉnʉ ke,\x - \xo 1:5 \xt Aisaya 55:4; Eren 89:27\x* 
\v 6 mɨrɨpan uya use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan pe uku'sa' kon Papa itese' pɨ' te'to' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉkʉipʉnʉ, apiyo' pe e'nɨto' pe—tɨwɨ Sises Kʉrai ku'to' eke pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ meruntɨ pe iye'to' nesii, itiwano' pe inke rɨ! Amen.\x - \xo 1:6 \xt E'sotas 19:6; Isenpoikasa' 5:10\x* 
\q1  
\v 7 Entɨ'! Kapuru' yau iyepʉ! 
\q2 Tanporon kon uya rɨ ento' oton, 
\q1 apurupɨ'nin nʉ'san pokon pe rɨ. 
\q2 Tanporon kon non po te'san ka'pon amʉ' ukaranto' oton tʉuta'kwarʉkai' iwenai. 
\qr Mɨrɨ kasa iye'to' oton! Amen.\x - \xo 1:7 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:13; Sakaraya 12:10; Ma'siu 24:30; Ma' 13:26; Ʉru' 21:27; Isaan 19:34, 37; 1 Tesaroni'ka 4:17\x* 
\p  
\v 8 “Urɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Arʉ'pa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Omeka,” ta Itepuru Papa Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye' uya, “moro te'sen, moro iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuye'ton,” uya ta.\x - \xo 1:8 \xt E'sotas 3:14; Isenpoikasa' 22:13\x* 
\s1 Ka'pon, Papa Winon Waraino 
\p  
\v 9 Isaan urɨ, ɨrui kon, Sises a'kɨrɨ esi koro'tau ɨtonpa kon pe esi serɨ ɨsɨ a'kʉre'tɨ pɨ', esa' wannɨ pe iye'to' yawon kon pe te'san neporonʉ, opa'wʉ Pa'tʉmos itese' po inonkasa' pe esi'pʉ Papa maimu mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'napairon Sises nenpoika'pʉ ekama uya pɨ'.  
\v 10 Itepuru weyu a'tai, Ita'kwarʉ yau esi'pʉ, mɨrɨ yau eke main tʉronpi' maimu waraino eta'pʉ uya uya'poi winɨ.  
\v 11 “Menyai'ne' imenuka' kareta pɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ menno'pɨtʉi' 7 kaisaron so'si ya'ne E'pe'sas pona, Simerʉna pona, Porʉkaman pona, Taya'tira pona, Sarʉtes pona, Piraterʉ'piya pona, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Irawote'siya pona,” tawon. 
\p  
\v 12 Era'tɨ'pʉ ɨnʉ' uya uyauro'ka tukai' ense'na. Era'tɨsa' a'tai, 7 kaisaron korʉ pun konekasa' raan'pu apon ton ene'pʉ uya.  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ ton koro'tau ka'pon, Papa winon waraino ene'pʉ uya, ipon esi'pʉ i'ta pʉ'kʉ pona mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ korʉ pun konekasa' pe iyawoino esi'pʉ.\f + \fr 1:13 \ft Taniyerʉ 7:13; 10:5.\f* 
\v 14 I'pai i'po' esi'pʉ aimu'ne karimeru i'po' kasa mɨrɨ pe pʉra sino tato' kasa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itenu amʉ' e'werouwerouma'pʉ apo' kasa.  
\v 15 I'ta amʉ' esi'pʉ karukuri epo'tɨ urentasa' kasa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tuna ena kasa imaimu useta'pʉ.\x - \xo 1:15 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:9; 10:6\x*\x - \xo 1:15 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 1:24; 43:2; 2 Estʉras 6:17\x* 
\v 16 7 kaisaron kon sirikɨ amʉ' a'sisa' iya esi'pʉ temiyatʉ enwo'netʉ winɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyɨkena', ɨsi'ratoi pokon iyɨ supara epa'ka'pʉ inta yapai. Itemʉ' esi'pʉ a'kwa pe kuru rɨ wʉi enu esi a'ne' pe a'taino kasa. 
\p  
\v 17 Ensa' uya a'tai, i'ta piyau uta'mo'ka'pʉ eke' kasa. Mɨrɨpan uya temiyatʉ enwo'netʉ ke uya'pɨtʉ'pʉ, “Kenari'nʉmʉi. Urɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Wapiyaro', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Iu'matʉ.\x - \xo 1:17 \xt Aisaya 44:6; 48:12; 2 Estʉras 10:30; Isenpoikasa' 2:8; 22:13\x* 
\v 18 Nurɨne e'ai'; iyeri'sa' rʉ'pʉ urɨ e'tane, nurɨne e'ai' inkero', inkero' pe rɨ! Ekota'man pata'se' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eri'nɨto' kii esa' pe e'ai'. 
\p  
\v 19 “Imenukakɨ, ɨnene'pʉ, serɨ pe na'ne' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ tʉpo te'ku'ton.  
\v 20 Serɨ si ama'aino ekamanin, 7 kaisaron kon sirikɨ amʉ' uyemiyatʉ enwo'netʉ yau na'ne' nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisaron korʉ pun konekasa' raan'pu apon ton: Kamoro 7 kaisaron kon sirikɨ amʉ' esi 7 kaisaron so'si inserʉʉi amʉ'\f + \fr 1:20 \fq so'si inserʉʉi amʉ', \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq so'si nennokonʉ ton\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisaron raan'pu apon ton esi 7 kaisaron so'si amʉ' ekamanin pe. 
\c 2  
\s1 Main E'pe'sas Pona Kan 
\p  
\v 1 “E'pe'sas pon so'si inserʉʉi\f + \fr 2:1 \fq inserʉʉi, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq inennokonʉ; \ft v. 8, 12, 18 yau nɨrɨ.\f* ena' imenuka': 
\pi1 “Se ka'kɨ ɨmunkɨ amʉ' pɨ', tukai': Serɨ main esi 7 kaisaron kon sirikɨ amʉ' a'sisa' iya na'ne' temiyatʉ enwo'netʉ yau winon pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisaron korʉ pun ka'sa' raan'pu apon pe koro'tawɨrɨ nʉsayai'ne'.  
\v 2 Ɨnkupʉ'pʉ kon si'tuyai', sa'man pe rɨ ɨye'tʉrawasomasa' kon, ɨuseta'kasa' kon pʉra rɨ. Si'tuyai', ɨri ton anʉnsa' auya'nokon pʉra rɨ iyesi, itekare ekamai' enno'sa' kon ina tawon nan i'tupɨ'sa' auya'nokon kasi ye' ton pe.  
\v 3 Ɨuseta'kasa' kon pʉra iyesi, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsɨ rɨ a'kʉre'tɨsa' auya'nokon uyese' wenai, e'tane ɨye'nonkasa' kon pʉra iyesi. 
\pi1  
\v 4 “E'tane ipoken pʉra ɨwe'to' kon eposa' uya man: Wapiya ɨsi'nʉnkena' pe ɨwesi'pʉ kon kasa pʉra me'atʉi'.  
\v 5 Auta'mo'ka'pʉ kon awonsi'kɨ i'tutɨ'! Amakooi kon winɨpai era'tɨtɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wapiya ɨnkupʉ'pʉ kon kupʉ kon pa. Amakooi kon apai ɨyera'tɨ kon pʉra iyesi yau, ɨpiya'nokon uyepʉ mɨrɨ ipata'se' apai araan'puui kon apon amase'na.  
\v 6 E'tane wakʉ pe ɨku'to' kon ipɨkɨrɨ moro man: Ni'korai'tan amʉ' eseru ewaruma'tɨ auya'nokon, uyewaruma rɨ nɨrɨ. 
\pi1  
\v 7 “Tʉpana ke te'sen, tɨwɨ Ita'kwarʉ uya so'si ton auro'kayai'ne' etai. Kamoro entakanin nan repato' uya oton wakʉ, Papa pata'se' yawon uko'man nɨto' e' eperu ke to' uya ina'to' pe.\x - \xo 2:7 \xt Iseneses 2:9; Isi'kiyerʉ 28:13 (LXX); 31:8; 2 Estʉras 2:12; Isenpoikasa' 22:2\x* 
\s1 Main Simerʉna Pona Kan 
\p  
\v 8 “Simerʉna pon so'si inserʉʉi ena' imenuka': 
\pi1 “Se ka'kɨ ɨmunkɨ amʉ' pɨ', tukai': Serɨ main esi Wapiyaro' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Iu'matʉ, iyeri'sa' rʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuko'mansen nurɨne winɨpaino.\x - \xo 2:8 \xt Aisaya 44:6; 48:12; Isenpoikasa' 1:17; 22:13\x* 
\v 9 Si'tuyai', ayanpokʉmanin kon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ entu'ma' rɨ ɨwesi kon, e'tane imaminke' pe me'atʉi'. Ɨri pe rɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' pe te'ku'san usauro'sa' si'tuyai', e'tane kamoro pen nɨ, Se'tan\f + \fr 2:9 \fq Se'tan\ft —Makoi ese' isakon, \fq Papa eseru ewaruma'tɨnin \ft ta e'kwa pe; v. 13, 24 yau nɨrɨ.\f* usenupato' iwʉ' ton kamoro.  
\v 10 Ɨkota'mato' kon pɨ' kenari'nʉntʉu. Etatɨ'! Makoi uya ɨi'tuto' kon oton pariki'si ta' ɨtonpa kon ta'sise. 10 kaisa rɨ wʉi ɨyekota'mato' kon oton. Wakʉ pe upɨ' tʉuta'sii' e'tɨ' ɨyeri'to' kon nɨ e'sepotane, mɨrɨ a'tai ɨuko'manto' kon arʉkooi ke ɨrepa uya 'nokon mɨrɨ. 
\pi1  
\v 11 “Tʉpana ke te'sen, tɨwɨ Ita'kwarʉ uya so'si ton auro'kayai'ne' etai. Iyakon ite'kwa pe eri'nɨto' uya kamoro entakanin nʉ'san wɨto' oton pen.\x - \xo 2:11 \xt Isenpoikasa' 20:14; 21:8\x* 
\s1 Main Porʉkaman Pona Kan 
\p  
\v 12 “Porʉkaman pon so'si inserʉʉi ena' imenuka': 
\pi1 “Se ka'kɨ ɨmunkɨ amʉ' pɨ', tukai': Serɨ serɨ main, iyɨkena' ɨsi'ratoi pokon iyɨ supara esa' maimu.  
\v 13 Ɨuko'manto' kon pata'se' si'tuyai', Se'tan apon pata'se' yau. I'napai rɨ upɨ' auta'sisa' kon, upɨ' i'napairon tato' auya'nokon nonkasa' auya'nokon pʉra rɨ, Anti'pas, iyawɨrɨ kuru uyekamanin wɨnɨ to' uya koro'tau rɨ apata kon yau mɨrɨ Se'tan uko'manto' yau. 
\pi1  
\v 14 “E'tane ipoken pʉra ɨwe'to' kon eposa' uya man: Moro Peran eseru ku'nin nan man ɨ'koro'tau'nokon. Para' enupa'pʉ iya Esuwerʉ amʉ' e'makoimato' ipɨkɨrɨ ku'to' pe iya, ika'sa' ena' itʉsa' rʉ'pʉ pɨ' to' uta're'tɨto' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' ekumato' pe.\x - \xo 2:14 \xt Nonpa 22:5, 7; 25:1-3; Isu'taronomi 23:4\x* 
\v 15 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ Ni'korai'tan amʉ' usenupato' ku'nin nan moro man ɨ'koro'tau'nokon.  
\v 16 Era'tɨtɨ' amakooi kon apai. Ikupʉ auya'nokon pʉra iyesi yau, inke pʉra uyepʉ mɨrɨ ɨpiya'nokon to' ewa'nomase'na, mɨrɨ unta apai tepa'kasen supara ke. 
\pi1  
\v 17 “Tʉpana ke te'sen, tɨwɨ Ita'kwarʉ uya so'si ton auro'kayai'ne' etai. Kʉrɨ rɨ entakanin nʉ'pʉ repato' uya oton tonan tawon mana tato' kiyari ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aimu'nan tɨ' ke irepato' uya oton, emenna' ese' e'menukasa' ipɨ', tʉron kon ni'tunʉ pen nɨ, eponin nɨken ni'tunʉ.\x - \xo 2:17 \xt E'sotas 16:14-15; 16:33-34; Aisaya 62:2; 65:15; Isaan 6:48-50\x* 
\s1 Main Taya'tira Pona Kan 
\p  
\v 18 “Taya'tira pon so'si inserʉʉi ena' imenuka': 
\pi1 “Se ka'kɨ ɨmunkɨ amʉ' pɨ', tukai': Serɨ main esi Papa Mumu winɨpaino, apo' e'werouwerouma waraino itenu mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karukuri aku'nɨsa' kasa tʉurenpanpɨ'sen i'ta.  
\v 19 Ɨnkupʉnʉ kon si'tuyai', ɨusi'nʉnkato' kon, i'napai rɨ ɨwe'to' kon, ɨyepika'tɨto' kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuseta'kasen pe pʉra rɨ ɨwesi kon. Wapiya ikupʉ'pʉ auya'nokon entai serɨ pe mʉku'atʉi'. 
\pi1  
\v 20 “E'tane se man ɨri pe ɨpɨ'nokon e'ku'to': Kʉrɨ rɨ uri'san Isesaperʉ, pu'kena' pe te'ku'sen pɨrɨ'ka auya'nokon pʉra iyesi. Upoitorʉ ton enupa iya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' ano'ma iya to' ekumato' pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa pe itese' ika'sa' ena' itʉsa' rʉ'pʉ pɨ' to' uta're'tɨto' pe to' kupʉ iya.\x - \xo 2:20 \xt 1 Kin Amʉ' 16:31; 2 Kin Amʉ' 9:22, 30\x* 
\v 21 Tʉmakooi winɨpai iyera'tɨto' pe iweyu ke irepa'pʉ uya e'tane tekumato' ɨnnonkapai pʉra iyesi.  
\v 22 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', te'kwe' po takuru'ke iye'to' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo iya'kɨrɨ iyekumasa' kon pokon pe ipan pe e'ne' moronkato' pe to' uya inonka uya. Serɨ pe kuru serɨ kupʉ uya, ɨri ku'nin nʉ'san iya'kɨrɨ era'tɨ pʉra iyesi a'tai.  
\v 23 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iya'kɨrɨ te'san kanan tʉ'ka uya mɨrɨ, so'si ton uya i'tuto' pe urɨ esi ka'pon amʉ' ewan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' usenuminkato' i'tunin, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ akaisarɨ'nokon ɨye'ma uya 'nokon mɨrɨ ɨnkupʉ'pʉ kon pɨkɨrɨ rɨ.\x - \xo 2:23 \xt Eren 7:9; 62:12; Iseremaya 17:10\x* 
\v 24 Ta uya ɨmɨrɨ'nokon tonpa ton Taya'tira pon kon pɨ', ita'sisa' pʉra na'ne' nan isenupato' pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ isenupasa' pʉra na'ne' nan ama'aino kuru Se'tan eseru tato' pɨ'. E'tane ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, tʉron nɨ rɨ e'tape'ne' nonka uya pen serɨ ɨpona'nokon.  
\v 25 E'tane ɨpiyau'nokon na'ne' pɨ' ata'sitɨ' pana' pe uyepʉ pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ. 
\pi1  
\v 26-28 “Kʉrɨ rɨ entakanin nʉ'pʉ i'se e'to' kupʉ pɨ' iye'sa' iu'matʉ pona rɨ ena' eke pe e'nɨto' tʉto' uya oton ukʉipʉnʉ winɨpai uneporo'pʉ, ka'pon amʉ' tʉpataron kon esa' pe iye'to' pe— 
\q1 ‘Wa'ka pun konekasa' itɨɨi pe esii'ma to' esa' pe iyesi; 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' a'morʉka iya tawa ka'sa' ɨinɨ pe a'morʉka kasa.’\f + \fr 2:26-28 \ft Eren 2:8-9 (LXX)\f* 
\m Awanakʉi'no kaiyono' ke nɨrɨ irepa uya mɨrɨ. 
\pi1  
\v 29 “Tʉpana ke te'sen, tɨwɨ Ita'kwarʉ uya so'si ton auro'kayai'ne' etai. 
\c 3  
\s1 Main Sates Pona Kan 
\p  
\v 1 “Sates pon so'si inserʉʉi\f + \fr 3:1 \fq inserʉʉi, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq inennokonʉ; \ft v. 7, 14 yau nɨrɨ.\f* ena' imenuka': 
\pi1 “Se ka'kɨ ɨmunkɨ amʉ' pɨ' tukai': Serɨ main esi 7 kaisaron Papa A'kwarʉ amʉ'\f + \fr 3:1 \fq 7 kaisaron kon Papa A'kwarʉ amʉ'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq 7 e'to' airon iteseru Iya'kwarʉ.\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisaron kon sirikɨ amʉ' a'sisa' iya na'ne' winɨpaino. Ɨnkupʉnʉ kon si'tuyai', nurɨne ɨwesi kon tukai' ɨye'kupʉ kon e'tane iyeri'sa' pe ɨwesi kon.  
\v 2 Apakatɨ', moro iye'ku'sa' na'ne' imeruntɨtanʉ'tɨ', eri'nɨ poken na'ne'. Eposa' uya man ɨnkupʉ'pʉ kon esi iyenuka'sa' pe pʉra Papa, itese' pɨ' e'to' enu yau.  
\v 3 Ɨyenupa'pʉ kon iku'tɨ' ɨyenu kon yau eta'pʉ auya'nokon awɨrɨ, iyawɨrɨ e'tɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ amakooi kon yapai era'tɨtɨ'. Aupaka kon pʉra iyesi yau, ama' kasa ɨpiya'nokon uyepʉ mɨrɨ, ɨpiya'nokon uyepʉ weyu i'tuto' auya'nokon oton pen.\x - \xo 3:3 \xt Ma'siu 24:43-44; Ʉru' 12:39-40; Isenpoikasa' 16:15\x* 
\pi1  
\v 4 “Tu'kan kon pen Sates pon kon uya tʉpon kon oi'masa' pʉra man. Uya'kɨrɨ si to' usato' oton aimu'nan ya' tepontɨpɨ'se, apʉne pʉra mɨrɨ rɨ eponin nan ye' pe to' esi.  
\v 5 Kʉrɨ rɨ entakanin nʉ'pʉ epontɨto' oton aimu'nan ya', to' kasa. Moro uko'man nɨto' ese' apon yapai itese' kukato' uya oton pen. E'tane Ukʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itinserʉʉi ton uya eta tane uni'tunʉ kʉrɨ rɨ tato' uya oton.\x - \xo 3:5 \xt E'sotas 32:32-33; Eren 69:28; Ma'siu 10:32; Ʉru' 12:8; Isenpoikasa' 20:12\x* 
\pi1  
\v 6 “Tʉpana ke te'sen, tɨwɨ Ita'kwarʉ uya so'si ton auro'kayai'ne' etai. 
\s1 Main Piraterʉ'piya Pona Kan 
\p  
\v 7 “Piraterʉ'piya pon so'si inserʉʉi ena' imenuka': Se ka'kɨ ɨmunkɨ amʉ' pɨ' tukai': 
\pi1 “Serɨ main esi wakʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'napairon winɨpaino, Tepi' iwano' ki esa', a'kokanin pe iyesi ɨnʉ' uya rɨ a'koro poken pʉra, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'konin pe iyesi ɨnʉ' uya ɨ'rɨ a'koka poken pʉra.\x - \xo 3:7 \xt Aisaya 22:22; Isopu 12:14\x* 
\v 8 Ɨnkupʉnʉ kon si'tuyai'. Mʉra'ta si a'kokasa' uya man ɨiwano' kon pe ɨnʉ' uya a'koro poken pʉra rɨ. Aiko pe rʉ'kwɨ apana'pano kon man e'tane ayauro'kato' uya 'nokon awɨrɨ rɨ ɨwe'sa' kon man, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uyese' nonkasa' auya'nokon pʉra man.  
\v 9 Kamoro Se'tan\f + \fr 3:9 \fq Se'tan \ft - Makoi ese' isakon, \fq Papa eseru ewaruma'tɨnin \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* munkɨ amʉ', kasi ye' ton Esuwerʉ amʉ' pe te'ku'san kasi pe rɨ, ɨpiya'nokon to' uye'to' pe ikupʉ uya mɨrɨ a'ta kon piya' epeimase'na. To' uya si i'tu mɨrɨ ɨi'nʉnka kon uya tukai'.\x - \xo 3:9 \xt Aisaya 43:4; 49:23; 60:14\x* 
\v 10 Tʉuseta'kai' pʉra umaimu awɨrɨ e'tɨ' tasa' uya awɨrɨ ɨwe'sa' kon pɨ', amainanpa kon uya mɨrɨ ewankamanin weyu a'tai, non emʉ' pona nʉye'ai'ne' ka'pon amʉ' non pon kon i'tupɨ'se'na. 
\pi1  
\v 11 “Serɨ pe kuru uye'ai'. Ɨpiyau'nokon na'ne' imainanpatɨ', ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ayarʉkooi, kʉron mo'ka namai'.  
\v 12 Kʉrɨ rɨ entakanin nʉ'pʉ ku'to' uya oton ipiyaino pe, Papa, itese' pɨ' e'to' iwʉ' tau, mɨrɨpan uya inonkato' oton pen. Papa, itese' pɨ' e'to' ese' menukato' uya oton ipɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa pata'se' ese', emenna' Surusiran ese', tʉu'tɨ ton Epʉn winɨpai Papa, itese' pɨ' e'to' piyawonsi'kɨ; mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ emenna' uyese' menukato' uya oton ipɨ'. 
\pi1  
\v 13 “Tʉpana ke te'sen, tɨwɨ Ita'kwarʉ uya so'si ton auro'kayai'ne' etai. 
\s1 Main Irawote'siya Pona Kan 
\p  
\v 14 “Irawote'siya pon so'si inserʉʉi ena' imenuka': Se ka'kɨ ɨmunkɨ amʉ' pɨ' tukai': 
\pi1 “Serɨ main esi Amen winɨpaino pe, main awɨron, i'napai rɨ ekamanin\f + \fr 3:14 \fq ekamanin, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq esa'.\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon Papa nʉkoneka'pʉ esa' winɨpaino.\x - \xo 3:14 \xt Ipu'ketʉ 8:22\x* 
\v 15 Ɨnkupʉnʉ kon si'tuyai', i'tu uya ikomi' pe pʉra ɨwesi kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'ne' pe pʉra nɨrɨ. Tisakonʉ'kai' ɨwesi kon i'se e'ai'.  
\v 16 Apʉne pʉra mara rʉ'kwɨ a'ne' pe ɨwesi kon—a'ne' pe pʉra mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ikomi' pe pʉra ɨwesi kon pɨ', unta yapai ɨyeta'tanʉkʉ uya 'nokon mɨrɨ.  
\v 17 ‘Imaminkena' pe rɨ ina man; ipʉrataaike' pe rɨ ina man, i'se ina e'to' pʉra rɨ man,’ ta auya'nokon, e'tane ɨri pe ɨwesi kon, entu'ma' kuru rɨ ɨwesi kon, itimamin pʉra ɨwesi kon, ipon pʉra mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tenku'ne ɨwesi kon.  
\v 18 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', ayauro'ka uya 'nokon korʉ enna kon pa upiyapai, esukenan korʉ; mɨrɨ a'tai imaminkena' pe ɨwesi kon pa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aimu'nan pon ennanin pe, ɨyepontɨ kon pa, piyɨ'nʉ' na'ne' tense nɨpontɨ kon pa. Merʉ'sʉn kanan ennatɨ', ɨyenu kon ya' itʉrʉ kon pa; mɨrɨ a'tai, ennin pe ɨwesi kon pa. 
\pi1  
\v 19 “Uni'nʉnkanʉ ton pɨrɨ'kanin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' panamanin urɨ. Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', i'napairon pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ amakooi kon yapai tera'tɨi' e'tɨ'.\x - \xo 3:19 \xt Ipu'ketʉ 3:12; Ipuru 12:6\x* 
\v 20 Eta'! E'mʉ'sa'kasa' mʉra'ta nau iwɨpɨtʉ pɨ', mɨrɨpan ɨnʉ' uya rɨ umaimu etasa' uya mʉra'ta a'kokasa' yau, iya'kɨrɨ itiwʉ' ta' ewomʉ mɨrɨ, ipokon pe ata're'tɨse'na mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ upokon pe kanan ita're'tɨ mɨrɨ. \fig E'mʉ'sa'kasa' mʉra'ta nau iwɨpɨtʉ pɨ'.|src="CN02107B.tif" size="col" loc="REV 3:20" copy="David C. Cook" ref="3:20" \fig* 
\pi1  
\v 21 “Kʉrɨ rɨ entakanin nʉ'pʉ ku'to' uya oton upiyau iyereutato' pe uyapon po, entakasa' uya pɨ' Ukʉipʉnʉ piyau iyapon po ereutasa' na'ne' kasa. 
\pi1  
\v 22 “Tʉpana ke te'sen, tɨwɨ Ita'kwarʉ uya so'si ton auro'kayai'ne' etai,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 4  
\s1 Papa Apon Epʉn Pon 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, uyenu tʉrʉ'pʉ uya, mʉra'ta uta'kokasa' Epʉn po ene'pʉ uya urau. Mɨrɨ a'tai, wapiya uneta'pʉ wai, tʉronpi' warai maimu uya uyauro'ka'pʉ, “Enu'kɨ serɨ ya', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpɨ' enpoikato' pe uya te'ku'sen ton serɨ tʉpo,” tukai'.  
\v 2 Inke pʉra rɨ Ita'kwarʉ ya' ena'pʉ, mɨrɨ yau apono' esi'pʉ Epʉn po, mɨrɨpan po ka'pon ereutasa' esi'pʉ.  
\v 3 Iyereutasa' pe te'sen usene'pʉ enkena' pe tɨ', isaspa tato' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tɨ', kaneriyan tato' kasa. Apono' woi ɨkɨɨimɨ esi'pʉ tɨ', emɨrarʉ tato' kasa.  
\v 4 Apono' woi 24 kaisa rɨ apono' ton esi'pʉ, mɨrɨpan po'ne 24 kaisa rɨ itepuru ton ereutasa' esi'pʉ. To' epontɨpɨ'sa' esi'pʉ aimu'nan tʉpon kon ya', mɨrɨpan kon arʉkooi kʉron esi'pʉ korʉ pun konepɨ'sa' pe'ne to' i'pai po.  
\v 5 Apono' winɨpai kamiri' e'weuweuma'pʉ, ta'merunsen esi'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ korʉme e'toi'pɨtʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan apono' rau 7 kaisa rɨ raan'pu amʉ' epo'tɨ esi'pʉ. Serɨ ton si esi'pʉ 7 kaisaron Papa A'kwarʉ pe.\f + \fr 4:5 \fq 7 kaisa rɨ Papa A'kwarʉ pe; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq 7 kaisaron iteseru Iya'kwarʉ.\f*\x - \xo 4:5 \xt E'sotas 19:16; Isi'kiyerʉ 1:13; Sakaraya 4:2; Topi' 12:15; Isenpoikasa' 1:4; 8:5; 11:19; 16:18\x* 
\v 6 Apono' rau parau wanamari kasa tʉusensen esi'pʉ awai'nan tɨ' kʉrestarʉ tato' kasa. 
\p Mɨrɨpan a'sanau apono' woi iyesi'pʉ asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ', tenukena' nan to' pʉropo winɨ'ne mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' a'poi winɨ'ne.\x - \xo 4:6 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 1:22\x* 
\v 7 Wapiyaro' ene usene'pʉ rayan kasa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ite'ma'pʉ winon esi'pʉ paka mʉre kasa, to' osorʉwano esi'pʉ ka'pon emʉ' ke, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' asakɨrɨ'pano esi'pʉ imisimɨ arinta kasa.\x - \xo 4:7 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 1:5-10; 10:14\x* 
\v 8 To' kaisa rɨ to' apiri esi'pʉ 6 kaisa rɨ'ne, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' enu esi'pʉ to' oi'ne rɨ, to' apiri o'no'ne rɨ. Mɨrɨpan kon ereuta pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ wʉi nai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ewarupɨ nawɨrɨ rɨ: 
\qc “Wakʉ, Wakʉ, Wakʉ, 
\qc Itepuru Papa Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye', 
\qc moro iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ moro na'ne', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuye'ton,” 
\m ta tʉuya'nokon apai.\x - \xo 4:8 \xt Aisaya 6:2-3; Isi'kiyerʉ 1:18; 10:12\x* 
\v 9 Kamoro si asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' userenka apono' pon apurɨpɨtʉ pe, inama pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tenki ta tʉuya'nokon pe, tʉuko'mansen pɨ' inke rɨ, inke rɨ,  
\v 10 24 kaisaron kon itepuru ton e'sekunka'pʉ apono' po iyereutasa' piyau apurɨpɨtʉ pe, tʉuko'mansen inke rɨ, inke rɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya apono' rau tarʉkooi kon, kʉron nonkapɨtʉ'pʉ. 
\q1  
\v 11 “Wakʉ eponin ye' pe ɨwesi, ɨmɨrɨ, ina Epuru, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa, itese' pɨ' ina e'to', 
\q1 eke pe ɨi'tuto', anamato' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ meruntɨ eponin pe ɨwesi, 
\q1 tanporon nɨ esi pɨ' ankaa'pʉ pe. 
\q2 Amaimu awɨrɨ iye'ka'pɨtʉ'pʉ, 
\q2 tʉuko'manton kon pe,” 
\m ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\c 5  
\s1 Kareta Amon Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Karimeru Mʉre 
\p  
\v 1 Ene'pʉ uya iyereutasa' apono' po emiya enwo'netʉ yau kareta amon iye'menukasa' ɨsi'ratoi pɨ', 7 kaisaron a'si'to' ike ke a'si'sa'.\x - \xo 5:1 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 2:9-10; Aisaya 29:11\x* 
\v 2 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pana'pan inserʉ ene'pʉ uya, eke pe ekama'po'pʉ iya, “Ɨnʉ' nai wakʉ serɨ kareta amon a'si'sa' rʉ'pʉ i'kwɨ'nin pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'kokanin pe?” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 3 E'tane ɨnʉ' pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ Epʉn po, serɨ non po, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ non o'no,\f + \fr 5:3 \fq Serɨ non o'no; \ft mɨrɨ iyesi iyeri'sa' kon nono. (Apʉne Isenpoikasa' 1:18 enkɨ.)\f* mɨrɨ kareta amon a'koka ton mɨrɨpan yawon enton pe.  
\v 4 Mɨrɨ a'tai, ukaramʉ'pʉ ipan pe, apʉne pʉra ɨnʉ' rɨ wakʉ ka'pon e'seporo pʉra iyesi'pʉ a'koka ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ yawon enton.  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tikin nan itepuru ton tonpa uya ta'pʉ upɨ', “Kakaramʉi. Enkɨ! Moro rayan Isuta ko', Tepi' atʉ rʉ'pʉ uya iwapiya'kasa' man; kʉrɨ rɨ uya si 7 kaisaron a'si'to' ike i'kwɨtʉ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kareta amon a'koka iya,”\x - \xo 5:5 \xt Iseneses 49:9; Aisaya 11:1, 10\x* ta'pʉ iya. \fig Kareta amon a'koka iya.|src="CN01994B.tif" size="col" loc="REV 5:1-5" copy="David C. Cook" ref="5:5" \fig* 
\p  
\v 6 Mɨrɨ a'tai, karimeru mʉre ene'pʉ uya. Iye'mʉ'sa'kasa' esi'pʉ apono' aporo' po, asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itepuru ton esi'pʉ iwoi. Karimeru mʉre usene'pʉ iwɨsa' rʉ'pʉ pe, 7 kaisa rɨ iretʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisa rɨ itenu ton esi'pʉ. Mɨrɨ ton esi'pʉ 7 kaisaron kon Papa A'kwarʉ amʉ'\f + \fr 5:6 \fq 7 kaisaron Papa A'kwarʉ amʉ'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq 7 kaisaron iteseru Ita'kwarʉ.\f* serɨ non emʉ' kaisa rɨ enno'sa' kon.\x - \xo 5:6 \xt Aisaya 53:7; Sakaraya 4:10\x* 
\v 7 Itɨ'pʉ kareta amon mo'kai', apono' po iyereutasa' na'ne' emiya enwo'netʉ apai.  
\v 8 Mɨrɨ kareta amon mo'ka iya a'tai, asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 24 kaisaron kon itepuru ton e'sekunka'pʉ irakʉi'. Tanporo wai, a'pu tato' esa' pe to' esi'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' pʉsawʉ ton korʉ pun konekasa' yau a'po'na' nan esi'pʉ. Mɨrɨ esi Papa munkɨ amʉ' ɨpʉremasa' rʉ'pʉ.\x - \xo 5:8 \xt Eren 141:2\x*\fig Tanporo wai, a'pu tato' esa' pe to' esi'pʉ.|src="CN02108B.tif" size="col" loc="REV 5:8" copy="David C. Cook" ref="5:8" \fig* 
\v 9 To' userenka'pʉ emenna' eren pɨ':\x - \xo 5:9 \xt Eren 33:3; 98:1; Aisaya 42:10\x* 
\q1 “Wakʉ kuru ɨmɨrɨ, kareta amon mo'kanin 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'si'pɨ'sa' a'kokanin, 
\q1 apʉne pʉra iwɨsa' rʉ'pʉ pe ɨwesi, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨmʉnʉ ke ka'pon amʉ' enna'pʉ auya Papa iwano' pe, 
\q2 tanporon kon rʉko' rɨ, tʉmaimuron kon, tʉponaron kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' koro'tapai. 
\q1  
\v 10 To' konekasa' auya esa' wannɨ pe to' e'to' pe, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan pe, itese' pɨ' ina e'to' apiyo' pe, 
\q2 mɨrɨpan kon e'to' pe serɨ non esanon pe,”\x - \xo 5:10 \xt E'sotas 19:6; Isenpoikasa' 1:6\x* tukai'. 
\p  
\v 11 Uyenu tʉrʉ'pʉ uya, mɨrɨ a'tai tu'kan kon nɨ inserʉ amʉ' maimu eta'pʉ uya, tu'kan kon nɨ, tu'kan kon nɨ, 1,000 kaisaron kon pona rɨ 1,000 e'to' airɨ, 10,000 ite'kwa rɨ 10,000 kaisaron kon. To' e'soto'pɨ'sa' esi'pʉ apono' woi, ene amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itepuru ton woi.\x - \xo 5:11 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:10\x* 
\v 12 Mɨrɨpan kon userenka'pʉ eke pe: 
\q1 “Wakʉ kuru karimeru mʉre iwɨsa' rʉ'pʉ uya 
\q1 tʉpana'pano, timamin, tʉpu'ketʉ, tʉmeruntɨrʉ, 
\q1 tʉnamato', eke pe ti'tuto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tapurɨpɨ'to' eporo!” 
\m tukai'. 
\p  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tanporon kon nɨ Papa nʉkapʉ'san maimu eta'pʉ uya Epʉn po, non po, non o'no, parau kau, tanporon kon nɨ ka'tawon kon nɨ. To' userenka'pʉ: 
\q1 “Apono' po iyereutasa' na'ne' rɨ karimeru mʉre iwano' pe, 
\q1 apurɨpɨ'to', inamato', eke pe i'tuto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ meruntɨ nesii, 
\q2 inke rɨ, inke rɨ!” 
\m tukai'.  
\v 14 Asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' uya eikʉ'pʉ, “Amen!” Mɨrɨ a'tai si, itepuru ton e'sekunka'pʉ apurɨpɨ'se'na. 
\c 6  
\s1 A'si'sa' Ton 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ a'tai, karimeru mʉre uya 7 pan tonpa wapiyaro' a'si'sa' a'koka ene'pʉ uya. Mɨrɨ a'tai, tikin nɨ asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' tonpa usaurokʉ eta'pʉ uya korʉme kasa, “Ɨsi'kɨ!” tawon.  
\v 2 Uyenu tʉrʉ'pʉ uya, aimu'nan kaware ene'pʉ uya urau. Ipo te'sen uya urapa a'sisa' esi'pʉ, aro', kʉron tato' ke to' uya irepa'pʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ iwapiya'kanin ye' pe, iwapiya'kai'.\x - \xo 6:2 \xt Sakaraya 1:8; 6:3, 6\x* 
\p  
\v 3 Karimeru mʉre uya isakon pe te'sen a'si'sa' a'kokasa' a'tai, ene isakon uya, “Ɨsi'kɨ!” ta eta'pʉ uya.  
\v 4 Tʉron nɨ kaware epa'ka'pʉ, isuweyu. Ipo te'sen kupʉ'pʉ to' uya pana' pe iye'to' pe, e'wɨn nɨto' ku'to' pe iya serɨ non po tʉtonpa kon wɨto' pe ka'pon amʉ' uya mɨrɨpan repa'pʉ to' uya eke supara ke.\x - \xo 6:4 \xt Sakaraya 1:8; 6:2\x* 
\p  
\v 5 Karimeru mʉre uya itosorʉwano pe te'sen a'si'sa' a'kokasa' a'tai, ene amʉ' osorʉwano uya, “Ɨsi'kɨ!” ta eta'pʉ uya. Mɨrɨ yau, i'kʉrʉn kaware esi'pʉ. Ipo te'sen uya e'wemapɨ'nɨto' ipoi a'sisa' esi'pʉ tenau.\x - \xo 6:5 \xt Sakaraya 6:2, 6\x* 
\v 6 Mɨrɨ a'tai, main waraino eta'pʉ uya kamoro asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' koro'tau, “Aiko iten yai pʉrowa,\f + \fr 6:6 \fq aiko pe pʉrowa—tikin nɨ koini' \ft Kiri' maimu yau; 2 pon e'to' airɨ.\f* tikin nan wʉi yau e'tʉrawasoman nɨsa' epe'pʉ pe,\f + \fr 6:6 \fq tikin nan wʉi yau e'tʉrawasoman nɨsa' epe'pʉ pe \ft —pʉrata pun, tenariyas itese'\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ osorʉwau iten yai a'nai', pari tato' e'pasa' tikin nan wʉi yau e'tʉrawasoman nɨsa' epe'pʉ pe. E'tane karapa, are' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ waain kʉ'ma'tanʉkʉi!” tawon. 
\p  
\v 7 Karimeru mʉre uya isakɨrɨ'pano a'si'sa' a'kokasa' a'tai, ene amʉ' sakɨrɨ'pano uya, “Ɨsi'kɨ!” ta eta'pʉ uya.  
\v 8 Mɨrɨ yau, enkɨ'sɨimu'nan kaware ene'pʉ uya urau. Ipo te'sen ese' esi'pʉ Eri'nɨto', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ekota'man nɨto', Etis\f + \fr 6:8 \fq Etis - Hades \ft Enkeri'si maimu yau; iyeri'sa' kon nono. (Apʉne Isenpoikasa' 1:18 enkɨ.)\f* itese' esi'pʉ ite'ma'pʉ winɨ, a'ko pe. ¼ pe non esa' pe to' e'to' pe, to' kupʉ'pʉ to' uya tʉwɨsen pe to' e'to' pe supara ke, iwankan ke, paran ke, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ annin nan ene amʉ' ke.\x - \xo 6:8 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 14:21\x* 
\p  
\v 9 Karimeru mʉre uya 5 pe iku'nin a'si'sa' a'kokasa' a'tai, use'man nɨto' apon o'no ka'pon amʉ' a'kwarʉ ene'pʉ uya, iwɨpɨ'sa' kon Papa Maimu ekama to' uya pɨkɨrɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa nʉkupʉ'pʉ tʉpɨ'nokon ekama pɨ' to' e'sa' pɨ'.  
\v 10 To' ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ eke pe, “Meruntɨ Itepuru, wakʉ ɨmɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'napairon! Ɨ'rɨ a'tai non pon kon ka'pon amʉ' eseru aimenka auya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' kota'mato' auya ina mʉnʉ wenai?”  
\v 11 To' kaisa rɨ aimu'nan pon ke to' repapɨtʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon auro'ka'pʉ mara rɨ to' enkurunto' pe tʉtonpa kon ipoitorʉ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉtonpa kon to' esi'pʉ kasa iwɨton kon tu'kanoro e'seporo pona rɨ.\x - \xo 6:11 \xt 2 Estʉras 4:36\x* 
\p  
\v 12 Mɨrɨ a'tai, karimeru mʉre uya 6 pe iku'nin a'si'sa' a'koka ene'pʉ uya. Mɨrɨ yau ɨsɨ pe tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ esi'pʉ. Wʉi enu ena'pʉ i'kʉrʉn pe, isa'ka'si atʉ kapirita i'po' ke ikonekasa' kasa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo kapʉi ena'pʉ isuweyu pe mʉn kasa,\x - \xo 6:12 \xt Aisaya 13:10; Isowerʉ 2:10, 31; 3:15; Ma'siu 24:29; Ma' 13:24-25; Ʉru' 21:25; Isenpoikasa' 11:13; 16:18\x* 
\v 13 sirikɨ amʉ' uta'pokʉ'pʉ ka' poi non pona, iyakʉ'pʉsa' pen kiyari, pi' eperu a'pokʉ a'setun uya kasa.  
\v 14 Ka' pʉra iyena'pʉ kareta amon e'mepɨtʉ a'taino kasa, tanporo wʉ' amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ opa'wʉ ton utamapɨtʉ'pʉ tʉpata'se' yawonsi'kɨ'ne.\x - \xo 6:14 \xt Aisaya 34:4\x*\x - \xo 6:14 \xt Isenpoikasa' 16:20\x* 
\p  
\v 15 Mɨrɨ a'tai si kin amʉ' non pon kon, itepuru amʉ', soisa epuru amʉ', ipʉrataaikena' ton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke ton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon kon nɨ poitorʉ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' enawon kon pen nɨ e'so'nanpɨtʉ'pʉ tɨ' euta na'ne' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wʉ' po te'san tɨ' o'koi'ne.\x - \xo 6:15 \xt Aisaya 2:19, 21\x* 
\v 16 To' ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ wʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tɨ' amʉ' pɨ', “Ina pona ata'mo'ka', ina onankɨ kʉrɨ rɨ apono' po iyereutasa' na'ne' enu piyapai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre uya kota'man nɨto' piyapai!\x - \xo 6:16 \xt Oseya 10:8; Ʉru' 23:30\x* 
\v 17 Apʉne pʉra eke to' uya kota'man nɨto' weyu si serɨ yau man. Ɨnʉ' uya ken si a'kʉre'tɨ?”\x - \xo 6:17 \xt Isowerʉ 2:11; Mara'kai 3:2\x* ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\c 7  
\s1 144,000 Kaisaron Kon Esuwerʉ Ko' Amʉ' 
\p  
\v 1 Serɨ tʉpo, asakɨrɨ'nan kon inserʉ amʉ' ene'pʉ uya. To' e'mʉ'sa'kapɨ'sa' asakɨrɨ'nan non ekun airɨ'ne, asakɨrɨ'nan a'setun amʉ' a'si'pɨ'sa' to' uya esi'pʉ, non, parau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ yʉi posi'ma iya namai'.\x - \xo 7:1 \xt Iseremaya 49:36; Taniyerʉ 7:2; Sakaraya 6:5\x* 
\v 2 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉron nɨ inserʉ uyepʉ ene'pʉ uya wʉi enu uye'to' winɨpai, Papa nurɨnan uya a'si'pɨ'nɨto' ike esa' pe, mɨrɨpan ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ eke pe asakɨrɨ'nan kon inserʉ amʉ' pana ya' Papa nʉrepa'san to' pana'pano ke non mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ parau kota'mato' pe to' uya.  
\v 3 Inserʉ uya ta'pʉ, “Non, parau, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ yʉi kʉ'ma'tanʉ'tʉu Papa, itese' pɨ' ina e'to' poitorʉ ton ma'kʉi'tɨpɨtʉ to' pee'pɨ pɨ'ne a'si'pɨ'to' ike ke ina uya pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ.”\x - \xo 7:3 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 9:4, 6\x* 
\v 4 Kamoro Papa uya a'si'pɨ'nɨto' ike ke ima'kʉʉi'tɨpɨ'sa' kon to' pee'pɨ pɨ' tu'kanoro ekama'pʉ to' uya upɨ'. To' esi'pʉ 144,000 kaisa rɨ Esuwerʉ pon kon.  
\v 5 12,000 kaisa rɨ a'si'sa' kon esi'pʉ Isuta ko' amʉ', 12,000 kaisa rɨ Rupen ko' amʉ', 12,000 kaisa rɨ Kiyatʉ ko' amʉ',  
\v 6 12,000 kaisa rɨ Aisarʉ ko' amʉ', 12,000 kaisa rɨ Na'tari ko' amʉ', 12,000 kaisa rɨ Mana'sa ko' amʉ',  
\v 7 12,000 kaisa rɨ Simiyan ko' amʉ', 12,000 kaisa rɨ Ripai ko' amʉ', 12,000 kaisa rɨ E'sa'karʉ ko' amʉ',  
\v 8 12,000 kaisa rɨ Sepuran ko' amʉ', 12,000 kaisa rɨ Isose' ko' amʉ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 12,000 kaisa rɨ Pensiman ko' amʉ'. 
\s1 Anpisin Ton Ka'pon Amʉ' Aimu'nan To' Pon Ton 
\p  
\v 9 Serɨ e'ma'pʉ pe, anpisin, anpisin pe kuru rɨ ka'pon amʉ' amʉrasa' ene'pʉ uya urau, ɨnʉ' uya tanporo to' i'tu poken pʉra rɨ. To' esi'pʉ tʉponaron kon ka'pon amʉ' pe'ne rɨ tʉron kon ko' pe rɨ, tʉpataron kon winɨpaino pe rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉmaimuron kon pe'ne rɨ to' esi'pʉ. To' e'mʉ'sa'kasa' esi'pʉ apono' piyau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre piyau. To' epontɨpɨ'sa' esi'pʉ aimu'nan ya', temiyatʉ kon yau'ne patawa ye' apɨmu ton a'sipɨ'sa' to' uya esi'pʉ.\x - \xo 7:9 \xt 2 Estʉras 2:42\x* 
\v 10 Eke pe to' ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ: 
\q1 “Epika'tɨn nɨto' esi Papa, ina e'to' itese' pɨ' winɨpaino, 
\q1 iyereutasa' na'ne' apono' po, 
\q1 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre winɨpaino,” 
\m tukai'.  
\v 11 Tanporo inserʉ amʉ' e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ apono' woi, itepuru ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' woi. To' uta'mo'kapɨtʉ'pʉ temʉ' kon po apono' piyau, mɨrɨpan kon uya Papa apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ: 
\q1  
\v 12 “Amen! 
\q1 Apurɨpɨ'to' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pe iku'to', 
\q1 ipu'ketʉ, tenki tato', inamato', 
\q1 imeruntɨrʉ, ipana'pano 
\q1 nesii Papa iwano' pe tɨwɨrɨ rɨ. 
\q1 Amen!” 
\m ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ yau, tikin nan itepuru ton tonpa uya uyekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨnʉ' yan pʉsamoro aimu'nan ya' to' epontɨpɨ'sa' na'ne' nan? Nai yawon kon uye'sa'?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 14 “Mooi, mi'tuyai',” ta'pʉ uya ipɨ'. 
\p “Pʉsamoro kamoro ekota'man nɨto' yai iyepa'kasa' kon, tʉpon kon korʉkasa' to' uya aimu'ne'ne karimeru mʉre mʉnʉ ke.\x - \xo 7:14 \xt Taniyerʉ 12:1; Ma'siu 24:21; Ma' 13:19\x* 
\v 15 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', 
\q1 “Papa apon piyau to' esi mɨrɨ, 
\q2 to' esi i'se iye'to' kupʉ pɨ' wʉi nai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ewarupɨ nau, ipɨ' ɨpʉreman nɨto', use'man nɨto' iwʉ' tau; 
\q1 kʉrɨ rɨ apono' po iyereutasa' na'ne' uko'manto' oton to' pokon pe. 
\q1  
\v 16 Serɨ tʉpo, iwan pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tuna'kiri' ke to' enato' oton pen, 
\q1 wʉi enu mɨrɨ pe pʉra a'ne' pe te'sen uya to' kota'mato' oton pen,\x - \xo 7:16 \xt Aisaya 49:10\x* 
\q1  
\v 17 apʉne pʉra karimeru mʉre apono' aporo' po na'ne' e'to' oton to' esa' pe, 
\q2 to' ato' iya oton to'panʉ'nin non yai tepa'kasen tuna ka'. 
\q1 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa uya to' enu paru a'munakato' oton,”\x - \xo 7:17 \xt Eren 23:1-2; Aisaya 25:8; 49:10; Isi'kiyerʉ 34:23\x* 
\m ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 8  
\s1 7 Pe Iku'nin A'si'sa' 
\p  
\v 1 Karimeru mʉre uya 7 pe iku'nin a'si'sa' a'kokasa' a'tai, e'pana Epʉn e'paka'sa' esi'pʉ a'sa'mʉyai kʉra' emiya era'tɨto' airɨ rɨ.  
\v 2 Mɨrɨ tʉpo 7 kaisarɨ inserʉ amʉ' e'mʉ'sa'kasa' ene'pʉ uya Papa rau, mɨrɨpan kon repa'pʉ 7 kaisarɨ tʉronpi' ke. 
\p  
\v 3 Tʉron nɨ inserʉ, korʉ pun konekasa' a'po'nan yen esa' uyee'pʉ, mɨrɨpan e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ use'man nɨto' apon piyau. Eke pe a'po'nan ke irepa'pʉ tanporon Papa munkɨ amʉ' ɨpʉrema piri'nin pe iye'to' pe, mɨrɨpan po'tɨto' pe korʉ pun konekasa' use'man nɨto' apon po apono' piyau te'sen.\x - \xo 8:3 \xt E'sotas 30:1, 3; Emas 9:1\x* 
\v 4 A'po'nan epo'tɨ kɨrɨsin enuku'pʉ, Papa munkɨ amʉ' ɨpʉrema pokon pe, Papa rakʉi', inserʉ emiya apai.  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ tʉpo inserʉ uya a'po'nan yen anʉmʉ'pʉ mɨrɨpan uya apo' use'man nɨto' apon pon emaika'pʉ iya', mɨrɨpan eno'ma'pʉ iya non pona. Korʉme e'toi'pɨtʉ esi'pʉ, ta'merunsen esi'pʉ, kamiri' e'weuweuma'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ esi'pʉ.\x - \xo 8:5 \xt E'sotas 19:16; Ripaiti'kas 16:12; Isi'kiyerʉ 10:2; Isenpoikasa' 11:19; 16:18\x* 
\s1 Tʉronpi' Amʉ' 
\p  
\v 6 Kamoro si 7 pan kon inserʉ amʉ' 7 kaisaron tʉronpi' esanon e'kama'pʉ iturunpato' pe tʉuya'nokon.\x - \xo 8:6 \xt Ipu'ketʉ 11:5—12:2\x* 
\p  
\v 7 Wapiyaro' inserʉ uya tʉwaai turunpa'pʉ. Mɨrɨ a'tai tuna tɨ'mooi ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ apo' e'sumasa' mʉn pokon pe uta'pokʉ'pʉ non pona. Mɨrɨ yau ipʉ'kʉ pe rɨ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ non epo'tɨ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipʉ'kʉ pe rɨ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ rɨ yu' epo'tɨ'pʉ tanporo rɨ isenan nɨ wana' epo'tɨ'pʉ.\x - \xo 8:7 \xt E'sotas 9:23-25; Isi'kiyerʉ 38:22\x* 
\p  
\v 8 Itisakon nʉ'pʉ uya tʉwaai turunpa'pʉ. Mɨrɨ a'tai, eke wʉ' waraino epo'tɨ apo' ke eno'ma'pʉ to' uya parau ka'. Ipʉ'kʉ pe rɨ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ parau ena'pʉ mʉn pe.  
\v 9 Mɨrɨ a'tai, itonpa pe rɨ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ rɨ parau kau te'san eri'pɨtʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itonpa pe rɨ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ rɨ kanau epotorʉ'pʉ ton uma'ta'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 10 Itosorʉwano rʉ'pʉ uya tʉwaai turunpa'pʉ. Mɨrɨ a'tai, eke sirikɨ epo'tɨsa' ta'sʉrai' kasa uta'mo'ka'pʉ ka' ponsi'kɨ tuna tʉu'tɨsen ton tonpa ka', ⅓ e'to' airɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non yai tepa'kasen tuna ton ka'ne.\x - \xo 8:10 \xt Aisaya 14:12\x* 
\v 11 Sirikɨ ese' esi I'ne'.\f + \fr 8:11 \fq I'ne'\ft —itese' esi'pʉ \fq Wormwood.\f* Tuna tonpa, ⅓ e'to' airɨ ena'pʉ i'ne' pe. Mɨrɨ tensise tu'kan kon ka'pon amʉ' eri'pɨtʉ'pʉ, apʉne pʉra i'ne' pe tuna enasa' ke.\x - \xo 8:11 \xt Iseremaya 9:15\x* 
\p  
\v 12 Mɨrɨ tʉpo to' asakɨrɨ'pano uya tʉwaai turunpa'pʉ. Mɨrɨ a'tai, ⅓ e'to' airɨ wʉi enu pʉ'kʉ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ kapʉi pʉ'kʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ⅓ e'to' airɨ sirikɨ amʉ' tonpa ton e'wɨnɨ'pʉ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ rɨ. A'kwa pe iye'to' pʉra to' esi'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ⅓ e'to' airɨ wʉi naino pʉ'kʉ esi'pʉ iweyu pʉra, ⅓ e'to' airɨ kanan ewarupɨ pʉ'kʉ.\x - \xo 8:12 \xt Aisaya 13:10; Isi'kiyerʉ 32:7; Isowerʉ 2:10, 31; 3:15\x* 
\p  
\v 13 Uyenu tʉrʉ'pʉ uya, mɨrɨ yau imisimɨ arinta ka'tau maimu eta'pʉ uya, eke pe, “Ɨsɨ' kusa! Ɨsɨ' kusa! Ɨsɨ pe iyesi kamoro moro non po na'ne' nan pona, tʉronpi' uturumʉ useta a'tai osorʉwawon kon inserʉ amʉ' ne'kamayai'ne' iturunpa pɨ'!” tawon. 
\c 9  
\s1 5 Pe Inserʉ Amʉ' Ku'nin 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ a'tai, 5 pe to' ku'nin inserʉ uya tʉronpi' turunpa'pʉ. Sirikɨ ka' poi ita'mo'kasa' rʉ'pʉ non pona ene'pʉ uya; irepa'pʉ iya'mu pʉn iteuta\f + \fr 9:1 \fq iya'mu pʉn iteuta; \ft Apis—pata non a'mu yawon, ɨri a'kwarʉ ton a'sito' ya' to' kota'mato' u'matʉ pʉ'kʉ pona.\f* a'kokato' ike ki ke.  
\v 2 Iteuta a'koka iya a'tai, ikɨrɨsin epa'ka'pʉ iyapai, eke apo' epo'tɨto' en yapai ikɨrɨsin epa'ka kasa, wʉi enu mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka' ena'pʉ ewarupɨ pe iteuta kɨrɨsin ke.\x - \xo 9:2 \xt Iseneses 19:28; 2 Estʉras 7:36\x* 
\v 3 Kairau amʉ' u'tɨ'pʉ ikɨrɨsin koro'tau non pona, mɨrɨpan kon upana'panta'pʉ mɨnɨ' amʉ' pana'pano kasa.\x - \xo 9:3 \xt E'sotas 10:12-15; Ipu'ketʉ 16:9\x* 
\v 4 To' auro'ka'pʉ to' uya non pon wana' mɨrɨ pe pʉra ti'tui' pʉra rɨ yʉi muku'pɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra yʉi ma'tanʉkʉ to' uya namai', e'tane ka'pon amʉ' rɨken, Papa ma'kʉʉi a'si'sa' pʉra na'ne' nan to' pee'pɨ pɨ'.\x - \xo 9:4 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 9:4\x* 
\v 5 Kairau amʉ' uya ka'pon amʉ' eri'nʉ'kapɨtʉ namai' to' e'kupʉ'pʉ e'tane to' kota'mato' pe rɨken 5 kaisa rɨ kapʉi pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ. Mɨrɨ si e'ne' e'to' pe mɨnɨ' uya ka'pon si'posa' a'taino kasa.  
\v 6 Mɨrɨ 5 kaisaron kapʉi koro'tau uma'tan nɨto' warinpato' oton ka'pon amʉ' uya, e'tane to' uya epoto' oton pen; eri'pai to' e'tane, uma'tan nɨto' utɨpɨ'to' oton to' piyapai.\x - \xo 9:6 \xt Isopu 3:21; Iseremaya 8:3\x* 
\p  
\v 7 Kairau amʉ' usene'pʉ kaware amʉ' e'kamasa' te'wɨto' kon pe a'taino kasa, to' i'pai po'ne korʉ pun konekasa' waraino aro', kʉron tato' amʉ' esi'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' emʉ' usene'pʉ ka'pon amʉ' emʉ' kasa.\x - \xo 9:7 \xt Isowerʉ 2:4\x* 
\v 8 To' i'pai i'po' esi'pʉ uri'san amʉ' inse' kasa, to' yɨ esi'pʉ rayan yɨ kasa.\x - \xo 9:8 \xt Isowerʉ 1:6\x* 
\v 9 To' pʉropo nɨpon usene'pʉ wa'ka pun kasa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' apiri useta'pʉ kaware amʉ' uya tararan pi'sikʉ a'merumʉ ɨsewa'nomase'na to' utɨ a'taino kasa.\x - \xo 9:9 \xt Isowerʉ 2:5\x* 
\v 10 Taukʉ ke'ne to' esi'pʉ, si'pon nɨto' ike ipɨ'ne mɨnɨ' kasa. To' aukʉ yau to' pana'pano esi'pʉ ka'pon amʉ' kota'mato' to' uya ike 5 kaisa rɨ kapʉi yau.  
\v 11 Tepuru kon pe kin pe, iya'mu pʉn iteuta inserʉʉi ku'sa' to' uya esi'pʉ. Itese' Ipuru amʉ' maimu yau “Apatan,” mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Kiri' amʉ' maimu yau “A'poriyon”.\f + \fr 9:11 \fq Apatan \ft mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ \fq A'poriyon; \ft Ma'tanʉ'nin ta e'kwa pe.\f* 
\p  
\v 12 Tikin nɨ ɨsɨ, nari' kuru utɨka'sa' mɨrɨ; mɨrɨ e'ma'pʉ pe asa'rɨ ɨsɨ, nari' ton kuru tʉuye'ton e'ku'sa'. 
\p  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, 6 pe to' ku'nin inserʉ uya tʉronpi' turunpa'pʉ. Main eta'pʉ uya korʉ pun konekasa' use'man nɨto' apon ekun retʉ poi Papa piyau te'sen winɨpai.\x - \xo 9:13 \xt E'sotas 30:1-3\x* 
\v 14 Main uya ta'pʉ tʉronpi' turunpanin nʉ'pʉ inserʉ pɨ', “Kamoro asakɨrɨ'nan kon inserʉ amʉ' arankapɨ'kɨ eke tuna tʉu'tɨsen Yu'pʉretes itese' piyau auronpɨ'sa' kon.”  
\v 15 Asakɨrɨ'nan kon inserʉ amʉ' eukapɨtʉ'pʉ iya, to' e'kamasa' esi'pʉ serɨ a'taino pe, serɨ wʉi a'tai, serɨ kapʉi pɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ wʉipiya pɨ', itonpa pe rɨ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ ka'pon amʉ' tʉ'kato' pe to' uya.  
\v 16 Kaware pon kon soisa amʉ' tu'kanoro eta'pʉ uya, 200 meriyan kaisa rɨ to' esi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 17 Kaware amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' pon kon ene'pʉ uya, to' pʉropo nɨpon esi'pʉ isuweyu pe apo' kasa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉtarire, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kara'kwa' pe, sorʉ'pa tato' kasa. Kaware amʉ' i'pai esi'pʉ rayan amʉ' i'pai kasa, to' mʉta yai apo', ikɨrɨsin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ sorʉ'pa epa'ka'pʉ.  
\v 18 Itonpa pe rɨ, ⅓ e'to' airɨ ka'pon amʉ' wɨnɨ'pʉ mɨrɨ osorʉwawon paran; apo', ikɨrɨsin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ sorʉ'pa kaware amʉ' mʉta yai tepa'kasen uya.  
\v 19 Kaware amʉ' pana'pano esi'pʉ to' mʉta yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' aukʉ yau. To' aukʉ esi'pʉ ɨkʉi kasa ti'pai ke, mɨrɨpan kon uya ka'pon amʉ' i'kapɨtʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 20 Ka'pon amʉ' tonpa'san mɨrɨ paran nʉwɨnɨ'san pen era'tɨ pʉra iyesi'pʉ tʉnkoneka'pʉ kon piyapai. Makoi amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ korʉ ka'sa', sirʉpa ka'sa', karukuri ka'sa', tɨ' ka'sa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ yʉi konekasa' apurɨto' tʉuya'nokon ereutanʉkʉ to' uya pʉra iyesi'pʉ—ennin pen, etanin pen, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉusasen pen.\x - \xo 9:20 \xt Eren 115:4-7; 135:15-17; Taniyerʉ 5:23\x* 
\v 21 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ te'wɨto' kon, enwoke' pe te'to' kon, tekumato' kon, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ama' pe te'to' kon apai to' era'tɨ pʉra iyesi'pʉ. 
\c 10  
\s1 Inserʉ Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Kareta Amon 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉron nɨ eke inserʉ u'tɨ ene'pʉ uya Epʉn winɨpai. Iyepontɨsa' esi'pʉ kapuru' ya', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨkɨɨimɨ esi'pʉ i'pai epoi, itemʉ' esi'pʉ wʉi enu kasa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'si ton esi'pʉ apo' tepo'tɨsen esi ipiyaino ton kasa.  
\v 2 Aiko kareta amon a'kokasa' esi'pʉ itenau. Enwo'ne' winon ti'ta nonkasa' iya esi'pʉ parau po, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kami' winon ti'ta nonkasa' iya esi'pʉ non pona.  
\v 3 Mɨrɨ yau eke pe ikɨ'pɨ'nʉmʉ'pʉ rayan kasa. Ikɨ'pɨ'nʉnsa' a'tai, 7 kaisaron kon korʉme amʉ' usaurokʉ'pʉ.  
\v 4 To' usaurokʉ a'tai, imenuka pɨ' e'kama'pʉ, e'tane main eta'pʉ uya Epʉn winɨpaino, “Ama' pe serɨ 7 kaisaron kon korʉme amʉ' usauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ iku'kɨ, kʉ'menukai,” tawon. 
\p  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ a'tai, parau po mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non po iye'mʉ'sa'kasa' unene'pʉ inserʉ uya enwo'ne' winon temiyatʉ ɨnka'pʉ Epʉn winɨkʉi'.  
\v 6 Isaurokʉ'pʉ Papa ese' yau, inke rɨ tʉuko'mansen, Epʉn konekanin nʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo iyau te'sen, non konekanin nʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo ipo te'sen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ parau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo ikau te'san, “Iyenkurunto' pʉra man!” ta'pʉ inserʉ uya.  
\v 7 E'tane 7 pe te'sen inserʉ uya tʉronpi' turunpa a'tai, Papa uya ama' pe te'ku'to' ku'to' oton, tʉpoitorʉ ton, pu'kena' amʉ' pɨ' ekama'pʉ tʉuya kasa rɨ.\x - \xo 10:7 \xt E'sotas 20:11; Isu'taronomi 32:40; Taniyerʉ 12:7; Emas 3:7\x* 
\p  
\v 8 Main, uneta'pʉ Epʉn winɨpai uya kanan uyauro'kakaa'pʉ, “Enta mɨrɨ kareta amon imo'ka ta inserʉ enapai kʉrɨ rɨ parau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non po iye'mʉ'sa'kasa' na'ne',” tawon. 
\p  
\v 9 Inserʉ piya' utɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan ekama'po'pʉ uya aiko kareta amon tʉto' pe iya uyena', “Uyenapai imo'ka',” ta'pʉ iya upɨ'. “Ɨ'kɨ! Kata' pe iyena mɨrɨ ɨyewan yau, e'tane a'se'ku pe iyesi mɨrɨ anta yau, teusan kasa,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 10 Aiko kareta amon mo'ka'pʉ uya inserʉ enapai, mɨrɨpan ɨku'pʉ uya. A'se'ku pe iye'sonpa'pʉ unta yau, teusan kasa, e'tane enko'ma uya tʉpo, kata' pe uyewan yau iyena'pʉ.\x - \xo 10:10 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 2:8—3:3\x* 
\v 11 Mɨrɨ a'tai, upɨ' ta'pʉ, “Papa Maimu ekamaka'kɨ kanan tu'kan kon ka'pon amʉ' tʉponaron kon pɨ', tʉpataron kon pɨ', tʉmaimuron kon pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kin amʉ' pɨ',” tukai'. 
\c 11  
\s1 Asa'ron Kon Ekamanin Nan 
\p  
\v 1 I'tuto' yʉi ke urepa'pʉ. Mɨrɨ yau, main eta'pʉ uya, “Enta Papa ena' use'man nɨto' iwʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ use'man nɨto' apon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itau tʉwɨpʉremasan tu'kanoro mi'tui',” tawon.\x - \xo 11:1 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 40:3; Sakaraya 2:1-2\x* 
\v 2 “Ipʉrorooi rɨken kʉsi'tui, apʉne pʉra Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen ena' iye'tʉsa' mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya Wakʉ Pata\f + \fr 11:2 \fq Wakʉ Pata \ft - Serɨ serɨ esi Surusiran ekamanin pe.\f* wasa'pɨ'to' oton 42 kaisa rɨ kapʉi yau.\x - \xo 11:2 \xt Ʉru' 21:24\x* 
\v 3 Asa'ron kon uyekamanin nan enno'to' uya oton pon isa'ka'si ya' to' epontɨpɨ'sa', mɨrɨpan kon usauro'to' oton pu'kena' amʉ' pe 1,260 kaisa rɨ wʉi.”  
\v 4 Asa'ron kon uyekamanin nan esi mɨrɨ asa'ron are' e' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asa'ron raan'pu amʉ', Itepuru, non esa' piyau te'san.\x - \xo 11:4 \xt Sakaraya 4:3, 11-14\x* 
\v 5 Ɨnʉ' rɨ esi to' ma'tanʉkʉ i'se a'tai, apo' epa'ka mɨrɨ to' mʉta yai to' eyaton non ma'tanʉ'se'na. Serɨ kasa ɨnʉ' rɨ to' anma'tanʉ'paino nerikʉi.  
\v 6 To' pana'pano e'to' oton ka' a'konin pe tuna uyepʉ namai' Papa Maimu ekama pɨ' to' esi koro'tau. To' meruntɨrʉ e'to' oton tuna ra'tɨnin pe mʉn pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non pona ti'tui' pʉra rɨ paran ne'to' oton to' uya inke i'se te'to' kon awɨrɨ rɨ.\x - \xo 11:6 \xt E'sotas 7:17-19; 1 Sanwerʉ 4:8; 1 Kin Amʉ' 17:1\x* 
\p  
\v 7 Unkupʉ'pʉ ekama to' uya u'ma'sa' a'tai, ene, iya'mu pʉn iteuta yapai iyepa'kasa' uya to' ewa'nomato' oton. To' entai iye'to' oton, mɨrɨpan uya to' wɨto' oton.\x - \xo 11:7 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:7, 21; Isenpoikasa' 13:5-7; 17:8\x* 
\v 8 To' ekepu nonkasa' e'to' oton eke pata e'ma tau, kurusu' pona tepuru kon pokapɨtʉ'pʉ yau. Mɨrɨ pata ese' ekamanin pe to' nesakʉ'pʉ esi Satan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isi'.\x - \xo 11:8 \xt Aisaya 1:9-10\x* 
\v 9 Ka'pon amʉ', tanporo tʉponaron kon, rʉko' amʉ', tʉmaimuron kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉpataron kon koro'tapaino kon uya to' ekepu enpɨ'to' oton osorʉwau wʉi mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pʉre'po'si pʉ'kʉ pona iyema'sa' yau, to' ekepu u'na'tɨ to' uya i'se pʉra to' e'to' oton.  
\v 10 Ka'pon amʉ' non pon kon e'to' oton pori' pe pʉsamoro asa'ron kon eri'sa' pɨ'. To' uta're'tɨpɨ'to' oton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉtonpa kon amʉ' repapɨ'to' oton to' uya, apʉne pʉra kamoro asa'ron kon pu'kena' amʉ' uya ɨsɨ ne'sa' pɨ' ka'pon amʉ' pona. 
\p  
\v 11 Osorʉwau wʉi mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pʉre'po'si pʉ'kʉ pona iyesi tʉpo, use'netu'kan nɨto' uyee'pʉ Papa winɨpai, mɨrɨpan ewomʉ'pʉ to' ya', mɨrɨpan kon e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ. Tanporon kon to' ennin nʉ'san usi'nʉkʉ'pʉ ipan pe.\x - \xo 11:11 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 37:10\x* 
\v 12 Mɨrɨ a'tai, asa'ron kon pu'kena' amʉ' uya main eta'pʉ Epʉn winɨpaino, “Ɨsi'tɨ' serɨ ya',” tawon. To' eyaton non uya to' enpɨtʉ koro'tau, to' enuku'pʉ Epʉn pona kapuru' yau.\x - \xo 11:12 \xt 2 Kin Amʉ' 2:11\x* 
\p  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ a'tai kuru rɨ, ɨsɨ pe tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ esi'pʉ. 1/10 kaisa rɨ eke pata uta'morʉka'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7,000 kaisa rɨ ka'pon amʉ' wɨnɨ'pʉ tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ uya. Ka'pon amʉ' tonpa'san enari'nʉmʉ'pʉ ipan pe, mɨrɨpan kon uya eke pe Papa, Epʉn pon e'to' apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ.\x - \xo 11:13 \xt Isenpoikasa' 6:12; 16:18\x* 
\p  
\v 14 Itisakon ɨsɨ, nari' kuru utɨka'sa' e'tane; enkɨ, itosorʉwano rʉ'pʉ ɨsɨ, nari' kuru uye'nɨ pɨ' man serɨ pe rɨ marɨ. 
\s1 7 Pe Iku'nin Tʉronpi' 
\p  
\v 15 7 pe inserʉ amʉ' ku'nin uya wai, tʉronpi' turunpa'pʉ. Mɨrɨ yau, eke pe main useta'pʉ Epʉn po: 
\q1 “Serɨ non esa' pe Itepuru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Kʉrai esi weyu e'seposa' man, 
\q2 mɨrɨpan uko'manto' oton itesa' pe inke rɨ, inke rɨ,” 
\m tawon.\x - \xo 11:15 \xt E'sotas 15:18; Taniyerʉ 2:44; 7:14, 27\x* 
\v 16 Mɨrɨ a'tai 24 kaisaron kon itepuru ton tapon kon po iyereutasa' kon Papa piyau uta'mo'ka'pʉ temʉ' kon po, mɨrɨpan kon uya Papa apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ.  
\v 17 Se kasa ta'pʉ to' uya: 
\q1 “Itepuru Papa Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye', moro na'ne', moro iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ; 
\q2 tenki ta pɨ' ina man 
\q1 apana'pano apurɨsa' auya pɨ', 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ esa' pe ɨwesi pa ɨye'sara'tɨsa' pɨ'. 
\q1  
\v 18 Tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' usakorotasa'; kota'man nɨto' auya weyu e'seposa' pɨ', 
\q1 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyeri'pɨ'sa' kon eseru aimenkato' auya. 
\q2 Ɨpoitorʉ ton pu'kena' ton e'mato' auya weyu e'seposa', 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ ton ɨpoitorʉ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro ɨyese' namanin nan, eke ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aiko ton, 
\q1 kamoro non ma'tanʉ'nin nʉ'san ma'tanʉ'to' auya pe man,”\x - \xo 11:18 \xt Eren 2:5; 110:5; 115:13\x* 
\m ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 19 Papa ena' use'man nɨto' iwʉ' uta'koka'pʉ Epʉn po, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ekonekan nɨsa' en\f + \fr 11:19 \fq ekonekan nɨsa' en - ark of the covenant \ft ta e'kwa pe. Serɨ esi'pʉ 10 apiyontɨto' en mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa esi se yau tato' ekamanin pe.\f* usene'pʉ mɨrɨ tau. Mɨrɨ yau, kamiri' esi'pʉ, ta'merunsen esi'pʉ, korʉme e'toi'pɨtʉ esi'pʉ, tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pe tuna tɨ'mooi ton uta'pokʉ esi'pʉ.\x - \xo 11:19 \xt 2 Ma'kapis 2:4-8; Isenpoikasa' 8:5; 16:18, 21\x* 
\c 12  
\s1 Uri'san Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Urupere 
\p  
\v 1 Eke i'tuto' ipɨkɨrɨ usenpoika'pʉ ka' yau: Uri'san epontɨsa' esi'pʉ wʉi enu ke, kapʉi esi'pʉ i'ta o'no, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 12 kaisaron kon sirikɨ amʉ' aro', kʉron tato' esi'pʉ i'pai po.  
\v 2 Serɨ pe rɨ iyentu esi'pʉ, te'tinkasa' pɨ' ikɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ.  
\v 3 Tʉron nɨ i'tuto' ipɨkɨrɨ usenpoika'pʉ ka' yau: Eke kuru, isuweyu urupere esi'pʉ 7 kaisaron i'pai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 10 kaisaron iretʉ ton amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisaron aro', kʉron tato' esi'pʉ i'pai po'ne.\x - \xo 12:3 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:7\x* 
\v 4 Taukʉ ke ⅓ kaisa rɨ sirikɨ amʉ' tonpa mo'ka'pʉ iya ka' poi, mɨrɨpan kon eno'ma'pʉ iya non pona. Iye'mʉ'sa'kasa' esi'pʉ uri'san tentusen rau, imʉre anto' pe tʉuya iyentusa' a'tai.\x - \xo 12:4 \xt Taniyerʉ 8:10\x* 
\v 5 Mɨrɨpan entu'pʉ warawo' pe, tanporon pata esa' pe te'ton wa'ka pun itɨɨi pe. Imʉre anʉmʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan arɨ'pʉ Papa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyapon piya'.\x - \xo 12:5 \xt Eren 2:9; Aisaya 66:7\x* 
\v 6 Uri'san ainʉmʉ'pʉ rɨmono' ta', Papa nʉkoneka'pʉ ipata'se' pe. Mɨrɨ yau imainanpato' pe 1,260 kaisa rɨ wʉi pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ. 
\p  
\v 7 Usewa'noman esi'pʉ Epʉn po. Maikarʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itinserʉʉi amʉ' uya urupere ewa'noma'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon ewa'noma'pʉ urupere mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itinserʉʉi ton uya.\x - \xo 12:7 \xt Taniyerʉ 10:13, 21; 12:1; Isutʉ 9\x* 
\v 8 E'tane pana' pe kuru pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon pata pʉra iyena'pʉ Epʉn po.  
\v 9 Kʉrɨ rɨ si eke urupere eno'ma'pʉ—kʉrɨ rɨ si penaro' ɨkʉi, Makoi, mɨrɨ pe pʉra Se'tan\f + \fr 12:9 \fq Se'tan \ft - Makoi ese' isakon, \fq Papa eseru ewaruma'tɨnin \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* itese', tanporo serɨ non ano'manin. Serɨ non pona eno'ma'pʉ tanporo itinserʉʉi amʉ' pokon pe.\x - \xo 12:9 \xt Iseneses 3:1; Ʉru' 10:18\x* 
\v 10 Mɨrɨ a'tai, eke main eta'pʉ uya Epʉn po, se kasa tawon: 
\q1 “Serɨ si Papa uya pika'tɨn nɨto' uye'sa' man, Papa uya tʉpana'pano enpoikasa' kin pe te'to'. 
\q2 Pana' pe te'to' enpoikasa' Inanʉmʉ'pʉ, Kʉrai uya. 
\q1 Utonpa kon amʉ' sapema pɨ' te'sen, 
\q2 Papa piyawonsi'kɨ to' sapema pɨ' wʉi mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ewarupɨ kaisa rɨ 
\q2 eno'masa' man Epʉn poi.\x - \xo 12:10 \xt Isopu 1:9-11; Sakaraya 3:1\x* 
\q1  
\v 11 Utonpa kon uya entakasa' 
\q2 karimeru mʉre mʉnʉ ke 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'napairon to' nekamanʉ ke, 
\q1 mɨrɨpan kon uya tʉuko'manto' kon tʉrʉ'pʉ 
\q2 tʉusi'nʉmai' pʉra tʉuma'tato' kon pe. 
\q1  
\v 12 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', pori' pe e'tɨ', Epʉn amʉ' 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyau te'san! 
\q1 E'tane ɨsɨ, nari' yau kuru me'atʉi' non mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ parau, 
\q2 apʉne pʉra Makoi u'tɨsa' pɨ' ɨpiya'nokon, 
\q1 mɨrɨpan usakorotasa', 
\q2 apʉne pʉra a'ko pe tʉweyu enasa' i'tu tʉuya pɨ',” 
\m tawon. 
\p  
\v 13 Non pona teno'masa' i'tusa' tʉuya a'tai, urupere e'sara'tɨ'pʉ uri'san, warawo' pe iyentusa' rʉ'pʉ e'ma'pʉka pɨ'.  
\v 14 E'tane eke imisimɨ apiri ke uri'san repa'pʉ iyarintato' pe ipata'se' pe ikonekasa' ya' rɨmono' ta'. Mɨrɨ yau iko'manto' pe osorʉwau wʉipiya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 6 kaisa rɨ kapʉi pʉ'kʉ pona, urupere uya eporo poken pʉra.\x - \xo 12:14 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:25; 12:7\x* 
\v 15 Mɨrɨ a'tai, urupere uya tuna enpa'ka'pʉ tʉnta yapai, eke tuna tʉu'tɨsen pe uri'san e'ma'pʉ winɨ, siya rɨ uri'san ato' pe iya.  
\v 16 E'tane non uya uri'san pika'tɨ'pʉ, tʉnta kari'ma'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan uya tuna tʉu'tɨsen, urupere mʉta yapai tepa'kasen enko'ma'pʉ.  
\v 17 Urupere usakorotasa' esi'pʉ uri'san pɨ', mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ ipayan ton panta'mase'na tanporo Papa Maimu apurɨnin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe te'san i'napairon Sises nenpoika'pʉ awɨrɨ.  
\v 18 Urupere e'mʉ'sa'kasa' esi'pʉ\f + \fr 12:18 \fq Urupere e'mʉ'sa'kasa' esi'pʉ; \ft Tʉron nɨ ton emen imenukasa' yau, \fq E'mʉ'sa'kasa' esi'pʉ\f* parau e'pi po. 
\c 13  
\s1 Ene Parau Kapaino 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, ene usenpo ene'pʉ uya parau kapai. 10 kaisa rɨ iretʉ amʉ' esi'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisa rɨ i'pai amʉ', 10 kaisa rɨ aro', kʉron tato' amʉ' esi'pʉ iretʉ po'ne, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa sapemato' ese' ton e'menukasa' esi'pʉ i'pai pɨ'ne.\x - \xo 13:1 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:3; 2 Estʉras 11:1; Isenpoikasa' 17:3, 7-12\x* 
\v 2 Kʉrɨ rɨ ene unene'pʉ esi'pʉ kaikusi kasa, i'ta amʉ' esi'pʉ ene, perʉ tato' i'ta kasa'ne, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inta esi'pʉ rayan mʉta kasa. Urupere uya ene repa'pʉ tʉpana'pano ke tapon ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pe te'to' ike, ke.\x - \xo 13:2 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:4-6\x* 
\v 3 Tikin nɨ ene i'pai tonpa kuntɨpɨ'sa' ɨsɨ pe poken isene'pʉ, e'tane isepi'tɨsa' esi'pʉ. Tanporo non usewansiuka'pʉ mɨrɨpan kon utɨ'pʉ ene pɨkɨrɨ.  
\v 4 Tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' uya urupere apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ apʉne pʉra eke pe te'to' tʉsa' iya pɨ' ene ena'. Ene kanan apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya, “Ɨnʉ' nai ene waraino? Ɨnʉ' uya ipanta'ma?” tai'ma. 
\p  
\v 5 Ene repasa' esi'pʉ mɨ pe te'to' yau isauro'to' pe, Papa sapema pe rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pe te'to' yau rɨ iye'to' pe 42 kaisa rɨ kapʉi yau.  
\v 6 Papa sapema pe iye'sara'tɨ'pʉ; itese', ipata iko'manto' yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo rɨ Epʉn po te'san pɨ' ɨri pe isaurokʉ'pʉ.\x - \xo 13:6 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:8, 25; 11:36\x* 
\v 7 Papa munkɨ amʉ' ewa'nomato' pe iya irepasa' esi'pʉ to' entai iye'to' pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pe iye'to' ke irepasa' esi'pʉ tanporo rɨ irʉko' amʉ', tʉponaron kon, tʉmaimuron kon, tʉpataron kon epoi iye'to' pe.\x - \xo 13:7 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:21\x* 
\v 8 Tanporon kon non pon kon uya ene apurɨpɨ'to' oton—tanporon kon itese' pʉra na'ne' nan non e'kaa'pʉ awonsi'kɨ tʉuko'mansan ese' apon kareta pɨ', karimeru mʉre, iwɨsa' rʉ'pʉ iwano' pɨ'.\f + \fr 13:8 \fq tanporon kon itese' pʉra na'ne' nan non e'kaa'pʉ awonsi'kɨ tʉuko'mansan ese' apon kareta pɨ', karimeru mʉre, iwɨsa' rʉ'pʉ iwano' pɨ'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq iye'menukasa' rʉ'pʉ orʉ e'kaa'pʉ si'kɨrɨ uko'man nɨto' karetaai pɨ' karimeru mʉre iwɨsa' rʉ'pʉ iwano' pɨ'.\f*\x - \xo 13:8 \xt Eren 69:28\x* 
\v 9 Kʉrɨ tʉpana ke na'ne', tɨwɨ netai. 
\q1  
\v 10 Kamoro ta'sisan pe te'san, 
\q2 a'sito' oton kuru rɨ, 
\q1 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro supara ke tʉwɨsan\f + \fr 13:10 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' yau, \fq supara ke te'wɨsan; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq supara ke wɨsan \ft tawon esi.\f* 
\q2 wɨto' oton kuru rɨ supara ke. 
\m Serɨ esi Papa munkɨ amʉ' esi tʉuseta'kai' pʉra imoronkanin nan pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyawɨron kon pe to' esi i'se.\x - \xo 13:10 \xt Iseremaya 15:2; 43:11\x* 
\s1 Ene Non Apaino 
\p  
\v 11 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, tʉron nɨ ene epa'ka non yapai ene'pʉ uya. Asa'rɨ iretʉ amʉ' esi'pʉ karimeru mʉre retʉ kasa, e'tane isaurokʉ'pʉ urupere kasa.  
\v 12 Mɨrɨpan uya eke tʉpana'pano wapiyaro' ene winɨ tʉneporo'pʉ apurɨ'pʉ eke ton kupʉ pɨ'. Non mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo iyau te'san apiyo'ma'pʉ iya wapiyaro' ene ikuntɨpɨ'sa' usepi'tɨsa' rʉ'pʉ apurɨpɨ'to' pe to' uya.  
\v 13 Pʉse rɨ ene isakon uya eke tʉtʉrawasooi ton kupʉ'pʉ, apo' nu'tɨ'pʉ iya Epʉn winɨpai non pona ka'pon amʉ' uya entane.  
\v 14 Tanporo ka'pon amʉ' non po te'san enku'tɨ'pʉ iya, apʉne pʉra i'tuto' ipɨkɨrɨ tʉku'se wapiyaro' ene iwano' pe. To' apiyo'ma'pʉ iya ikuntɨpɨ'sa' rʉ'pʉ ene supara ke usepi'tɨsa', mɨrɨpan uko'mamʉ namato' ipɨ' pe, ipe ika'to' pe to' uya.  
\v 15 Ene isakon use'netu'kato' pe wapiyaro' ene kasa ika'sa' ya' to' uya iku'sa' esi'pʉ tʉusauro'sen pe iye'to' pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tapurɨpɨ'nin nan pen tʉ'kato' pe iya.  
\v 16 Ene uya tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' kupʉ'pʉ—aiko ton, eke ton, imaminkena' ton, entu'manin nan, poitorʉ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' enawon kon pen—e'ma'kʉi'tɨto' pe enwo'ne' winon temiyatʉ kon pɨ', mɨrɨ pe pʉra tʉpee'pɨ kon pɨ',  
\v 17 ɨnʉ' rɨ usenna pen, mɨrɨ pe pʉra kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' iyesi pen tʉma'kʉʉi ke pʉra kʉrɨ rɨ ene ese' mɨrɨ pe pʉra itese' nonpaai pʉra iye'tane. 
\p  
\v 18 Serɨ esi pu'kena' pe e'nɨ i'se. Ɨnʉ' esi yau tenu ke, tɨwɨ ene nonpaai i'tui, apʉne pʉra ka'pon nonpaai pe iyesi. Inonpaai esi 666. 
\c 14  
\s1 Iyepika'tɨsa' Kon Eremu 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ a'tai, karimeru mʉre e'mʉ'sa'kasa' ene'pʉ uya urau Sayan Wʉpʉ po. 144,000 kaisaron kon ka'pon amʉ' esi'pʉ ipiyau, itese' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ikʉipʉnʉ ese' menukanin nʉ'san tʉpee'pɨ kon pɨ'.\x - \xo 14:1 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 9:4; Isenpoikasa' 7:3\x* 
\v 2 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ main eta'pʉ uya Epʉn winɨpai. Eke tuna ena kasa iseta'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pe korʉme e'tʉrʉnpɨtʉ kasa. Main uneta'pʉ useta'pʉ wai turunpanin nan uya tʉwaai kon, a'pu turunpa kasa.\x - \xo 14:2 \xt 2 Estʉras 6:17\x* 
\v 3 Kamoro 144,000 kaisaron kon e'mʉ'sa'kasa' esi'pʉ apono', asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itepuru amʉ' rau, to' userenka'pʉ emenna' eren ɨnʉ' ni'tunʉ pen nɨ pɨ', kamoro rɨken nɨ non poi iyepika'tɨsa' kon usenupato' ipɨ'.  
\v 4 Kamoro ka'pon amʉ' esi uri'sami'si a'kɨrɨ iyekumasa' kon pen nɨ. A'pɨ' pʉra to' esi. Karimeru mʉre pɨkɨrɨ to' e'sa' mɨ airɨ rɨ itɨ a'tai. Ennasa' kon tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' koro'tapai, mɨrɨpan kon e'to' oton wapiya kuru Papa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre ena' tʉtʉsan pe.  
\v 5 Kasi ye' pe to' e'sa' pʉra rɨ iyesi, ɨ'rɨ rɨ ɨri pʉra rɨ to' esi.\x - \xo 14:5 \xt Se'panaya 3:13\x* 
\s1 Osorʉwawon Kon Inserʉ Amʉ' 
\p  
\v 6 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉron nɨ inserʉ apirinta ene'pʉ uya ka'tau. Inkero' wakʉ main esa' pe tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' non pon kon auro'kase'na—tʉpataron kon, rʉko' amʉ', tʉmaimuron kon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉponaron kon auro'kase'na.  
\v 7 Eke pe isaurokʉ'pʉ, “Papa inamatɨ', eke pe iye'to' apurɨpɨ'tɨ', ka'pon amʉ' eseru aimenkato' iya e'seposa' man, apurɨtɨ'. Kʉrɨ rɨ apurɨpɨ'tɨ' Epʉn, non, parau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non yai tepa'kasen tuna konekanin nʉ'pʉ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 8 Itisakon nʉ'pʉ uya wapiyaro' inserʉ e'ma'pʉka'pʉ, “Ita'mo'kasa' man! Eke Paperan uta'mo'kasa' man! Tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' o'pasa' iya tʉyuku waain ke to' uya ensito' pe. Kata'pan tekuma euku, waain ke to' o'pasa' iya,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:8 \xt Aisaya 21:9; Iseremaya 51:8; Isenpoikasa' 18:2\x* 
\p  
\v 9 Itosorʉwano rʉ'pʉ uya wapiyaro' kon asa'ron kon inserʉ amʉ' e'ma'pʉka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya eke pe, “Ɨnʉ' rɨ ene mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipe ika'sa' rʉ'pʉ apurɨpɨ'nin nʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ima'kʉʉi menukanin nʉ'pʉ tʉpee'pɨ pɨ' mɨrɨ pe pʉra temiyatʉ pɨ',  
\v 10 uya Papa sakorooi euku, waain ensito' oton, kota'man nɨto' tʉuya pʉsawʉ ya' inma'pʉ. Tanporon kon serɨ ku'nin nʉ'san ekota'mato' oton sorʉ'pa epo'tɨ yau wakʉ ton inserʉ amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre uya enpɨ'tane.\x - \xo 14:10 \xt Iseneses 19:24; Aisaya 51:17; Isi'kiyerʉ 38:22\x* 
\v 11 Apo' to' po'tɨnin kɨrɨsin ekainʉnto' oton inke rɨ. Kamoro ene mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipe ika'sa' apurɨpɨ'nin nʉ'san mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ima'kʉʉi menukanin nʉ'san umoronka'to' oton pen, ewarupɨ nau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wʉi nai rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:11 \xt Aisaya 34:10\x* 
\v 12 Serɨ esi Papa munkɨ amʉ' esi tʉuseta'kai' pʉra imoronkanin nan pe to' esi i'se, kamoro Papa maimu awɨron kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'napai rɨ te'san Sises pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ a'tai, main eta'pʉ uya Epʉn winɨpai, “Imenuka',” ta'pʉ iya, “Pori' pe kuru kamoro esi mɨrɨ serɨ tʉpo teri'ton kon Itepuru tʉrawasooi pe esii'ma.” 
\p “Ewai',” ta'pʉ Ita'kwarʉ uya, “Tʉumoronka'to' kon eposa' to' uya tʉtʉrawasooi kon apai, mɨrɨpan kon nʉkupʉ'pʉ utɨ to' pɨkɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Non Akʉ'pʉsa' Anʉmʉ 
\p  
\v 14 Uyenu tʉrʉ'pʉ uya, aimu'nan kapuru' ene'pʉ uya urau. Mɨrɨ po ka'pon, Papa winon waraino\f + \fr 14:14 \ft Taniyerʉ 7:13\f* ereutasa' ene'pʉ uya. Korʉ pun konekasa' aro' kʉron pe i'pai po mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyɨkena' mariya, si'kʉrʉ tato' itenau.  
\v 15 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉron nɨ inserʉ epa'ka'pʉ Papa ena' use'man nɨto', ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' tapai, mɨrɨpan uya eke pe kapuru' po iyereutasa' auro'ka'pʉ, “Amariyarʉ, si'kʉrʉ apurɨkɨ, kiyari akʉ'pʉsa' anʉnkɨ, iweyu e'seposa' man non akʉ'pʉsa' a'tɨto' pe,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:15 \xt Isowerʉ 3:13\x* 
\v 16 Mɨrɨ a'tai, kapuru' po iyereutasa' uya tʉmariyarʉ, si'kʉrʉ ari'ma'pʉ non epoi. Mɨrɨ a'tai nin si, non akʉ'pʉsa' uta'tɨ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 17 Tʉron nɨ kanan inserʉ epa'ka'pʉ Papa ena' use'man nɨto', ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ', Epʉn pon tapai, mɨrɨpan esi'pʉ iyɨkena' rɨ marɨ si'kʉrʉ esa' pe.  
\v 18 Tʉron nɨ kanan inserʉ, apo' esa' epa'ka'pʉ use'man nɨto' apon winɨpai, eke pe ikɨ'pɨ'nʉmʉ'pʉ iyɨkena' si'kʉrʉ esa' inserʉ uya etato' pe, “Amariyarʉ, si'kʉrʉ apurɨkɨ kʉre' kiyari a'tɨkɨ umɨ non pon yawon apʉne pʉra iyakʉ'pʉka'sa' mɨrɨ,” tawon.  
\v 19 Mɨrɨ yau, inserʉ uya tʉmariyarʉ, si'kʉrʉ ari'ma'pʉ non pona, mɨrɨpan uya kiyari, kʉre' eperu a'tɨ'pʉ ite' poi, mɨrɨpan eno'ma'pʉ iya eke Papa uya kota'man nɨto' kasu'kato' en ya'.  
\v 20 Kiyari, kʉre' eperu ekasu'ka'pʉ ikasu'kato' yai, eke pata yau pʉra, mʉn epa'ka'pʉ ikasu'kato' yapai i'mʉnpʉ pe 1,600 kaisa rɨ yʉi epotorʉ'pʉ pe ikusano\f + \fr 14:20 \fq 1,600 kaisa rɨ yʉi epotorʉ'pʉ pe ikusano; \ft 160 mayirʉ e'to' airɨ.\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 5 pi' kaisa rɨ i'na', kaware mʉta yawon ato' ipɨ' kusano airɨ. \fig iyɨkena' mariya, si'kʉrʉ tato'|src="CN02109B.tif" size="col" loc="REV 14:14-20" copy="David C. Cook" ref="14:14" \fig* 
\c 15  
\s1 7 Kaisaron Kon Inserʉ Amʉ' 7 Kaisaron Paran Amʉ' Esanon 
\p  
\v 1 Tʉron nɨ i'tuto' ipɨkɨrɨ ene'pʉ uya ka' yau, eke, a'kwarʉpɨ'nin nɨ: 7 kaisaron kon inserʉ amʉ' esi'pʉ 7 kaisaron paran amʉ' u'matʉ esanon, apʉne pʉra Papa uya kota'man nɨto' u'ma'sa' ekamanin pe iyesi'pʉ.  
\v 2 Mɨrɨ yau, wanamari kasa tʉusensen parau ene'pʉ uya apo' pokon pe iye'sumasa'. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro kanan ene mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipe ika'sa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ nonpa pe itese' isenpoikasa' entai iye'sa' kon ene'pʉ uya. To' e'mʉ'sa'kasa' esi'pʉ awai'nan wanamari waraino parau e'pi po, Papa uya tʉrepa'pʉ kon tʉwaai kon, a'pu esa' pe'ne.  
\v 3 Mosi', Papa poitorʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre eremu pɨ' to' userenka esi'pʉ:\x - \xo 15:3 \xt E'sotas 15:1\x* 
\q1 “Itepuru Papa Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye', 
\q2 eke pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'kwarʉpɨ'nin pe kuru Ɨnkupʉnʉ man. 
\q1 Kin, tʉpataron kon iwano', 
\q2 ipoken mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'napai rɨ ɨyeseru esi. 
\q1  
\v 4 Oso sɨ! Itepuru, ɨnʉ' uya pe' anama pen nɨ? 
\q2 Ɨnʉ' esi, eke pe ɨyese' e'to' ɨnekamapai pʉra? 
\q1 Ɨmɨrɨ rɨken nɨ kʉrɨ rɨ wakʉ. 
\q1 Tanporon kon tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' uye'to' oton 
\q2 ayapurɨpɨ'se'na, 
\q1 apʉne pʉra ipokena' ɨyeseru usenpoikasa' man,” 
\m tawon pɨ'.\x - \xo 15:4 \xt Iseremaya 10:7; Eren 86:9\x* 
\p  
\v 5 Serɨ e'ma'pʉ ta', Epʉn po Papa ena' use'man nɨto', ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ', Ta'porin, mɨrɨ si Papa esi moro ekamanin pe te'sen uta'koka ene'pʉ uya.\x - \xo 15:5 \xt E'sotas 38:21\x* 
\v 6 Kamoro 7 kaisaron kon inserʉ amʉ' 7 kaisaron paran esanon epa'ka'pʉ use'man nɨto' iwʉ' tapai. To' epontɨpɨ'sa' esi'pʉ sirɨn pan pon renen tato' ya', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ korʉ pun konekasa' pokʉrʉ kasa ke to' utawoino'tɨpɨ'sa' esi'pʉ.  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ yau asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' tonpa uya 7 kaisaron kon inserʉ amʉ' repa'pʉ 7 kaisaron korʉ pun ka'sa' pʉsau pe'ne ke. Papa uya kota'man nɨto' ke'ne iyepe'tɨpɨ'sa', Papa inke rɨ tʉuko'mansen.  
\v 8 Papa ena' use'man nɨto' iwʉ' epe'tɨsa' esi'pʉ ikɨrɨsin Papa a'kwarii mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipana'pano ke, ɨnʉ' rɨ ewomʉ pʉra iyesi'pʉ ita' 7 kaisaron paran i'ma'ka 7 kaisaron kon inserʉ amʉ' uya pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ.\x - \xo 15:8 \xt E'sotas 40:34; 1 Kin Amʉ' 8:10-11; 2 Kʉrono'kʉrʉs 5:13-14; Aisaya 6:4\x* 
\c 16  
\s1 Papa Uya Kota'man Nɨto' En Ton 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ yau eke main eta'pʉ uya Papa ena' use'man nɨto' iwʉ' tapai 7 pan kon inserʉ amʉ' auro'ka iya, “Entantɨ', Papa uya kota'man nɨto' en amʉ' 7 kaisaron i'kwanpɨ'tantɨ' non pona,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 2 Wapiyaro' inserʉ utɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ti'sawʉ yawon i'kwamʉ'pʉ non pona. Ɨri mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ e'ne' ton ere' amʉ' epa'ka'pʉ ene ma'kʉʉi eponin nʉ'san pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipe ika'sa' apurɨpɨ'nin nʉ'san pɨ'.\x - \xo 16:2 \xt E'sotas 9:10\x* 
\p  
\v 3 Itisakon nʉ'pʉ uya ti'sawʉ yawon i'kwamʉ'pʉ parau ka'. Tuna era'tɨ'pʉ iyeri'sa' ka'pon mʉnʉ kasa, mɨrɨpan tanporo rɨ ikau te'san erikʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 4 To' osorʉwano rʉ'pʉ uya ti'sawʉ yawon i'kwamʉ'pʉ tʉu'tɨsen tuna ka' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non yai tepa'kasen tuna pona'ne rɨ, mɨrɨpan ton era'tɨ'pʉ mʉn pe.\x - \xo 16:4 \xt E'sotas 7:17-21; Eren 78:44\x* 
\v 5 Inserʉ tuna ton esa' pe te'sen uya ta eta'pʉ uya, 
\q1 “Wakʉ pe kuru me'ai', 
\q2 ka'pon amʉ' eseru aimenkato' auya yau, 
\q2 Ɨmɨrɨ Wakʉ, moro na'ne' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ moro iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ. 
\q1  
\v 6 To' uya wakʉ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pu'kena' amʉ' mʉnʉ ennoko'pʉ. 
\q2 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', mʉn ensito' pe to' uya iku'sa' auya, tepe'pʉ kon eporo to' uya,” 
\m ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ a'tai, use'man nɨto' apon uya eikʉ eta'pʉ uya, se tukai': 
\q1 “Ewai', Itepuru Papa Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye', 
\q2 i'napairon pe kuru rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe kuru ka'pon amʉ' eseru aimenkato' auya man,” 
\m tawon. 
\p  
\v 8 To' asakɨrɨ'pano rʉ'pʉ uya ti'sawʉ yawon i'kwamʉ'pʉ wʉi enu pona, mɨrɨpan a'ne' pe iyesi uya ka'pon amʉ' puto' pe iku'sa' esi'pʉ.  
\v 9 A'ne' pe iyesi uya ka'pon amʉ' puru'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya Papa ese' pa'nʉkʉ'pʉ, tanporo serɨ paran amʉ' esa' pe te'sen. E'tane tʉmakooi kon apai era'tɨpai pʉra to' esi'pʉ apurɨpɨ'se'na. 
\p  
\v 10 5 pe to' ku'nin inserʉ uya ti'sawʉ yawon i'kwamʉ'pʉ ene apon pona. Ewarupɨ pe itesa' pe iye'to' ena'pʉ. Ka'pon amʉ' uya tani kon i'kapɨtʉ'pʉ, apʉne pʉra e'ne' pe tesi kon pɨ'.\x - \xo 16:10 \xt E'sotas 10:21\x* 
\v 11 Mɨrɨpan kon uya Papa, Epʉn pon pa'nʉkʉ'pʉ e'ne' pe tesi kon pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ erekʉ' pe tesi kon pɨ'. E'tane ɨri teseru kon piyapai era'tɨpai pʉra to' esi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 12 6 pe to' ku'nin inserʉ uya ti'sawʉ yawon i'kwamʉ'pʉ eke tuna tʉu'tɨsen Yu'pʉretes itese' ka', mɨrɨpan mɨrɨ tuna a'muna'pʉ kin amʉ' wʉi enu uyepʉ winɨpaino kon uye'to' pe iyawɨrɨ.\x - \xo 16:12 \xt Aisaya 11:15\x* 
\v 13 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, osorʉwawon kon ɨri a'kwarʉ ton ene'pʉ uya, pɨrɨtuku waraino kon. To' epa'kapɨtʉ'pʉ urupere mʉta yapai, ene mʉta yapai, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ennakanin pu'kena' mʉta yapai.  
\v 14 Kamoro si esi'pʉ makoi a'kwarʉ ton eke tʉtʉrawasooi kon kupʉ pɨ'. Pʉsamoro osorʉwawon kon a'kwarʉ amʉ' utɨto' oton non emʉ' kaisaron kon kin amʉ' amʉranʉ'se'na to' usewa'nomato' pe Papa Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye', eke iweyu a'tai. 
\p  
\v 15 “Etakɨ! Ama' kasa uye'ai'! Pori' pe kuru kʉrɨ rɨ esi mɨrɨ te'nʉnse pʉra nenkurunyai'ne' tʉpon mainanpa pɨ' ipon pʉra tʉusarɨ namai' ka'pon amʉ' koro'tau tɨpiyɨtʉ namai',” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 16:15 \xt Ma'siu 24:43-44; Ʉru' 12:39-40; Isenpoikasa' 3:3\x* 
\p  
\v 16 A'kwarʉ amʉ' uya kin amʉ' amʉranʉkʉ'pʉ tanporo pata Amaketan tukai' Ipuru amʉ' nesakʉnʉ ya'.\x - \xo 16:16 \xt 2 Kin Amʉ' 23:29; Sakaraya 12:11\x* 
\p  
\v 17 7 pe to' ku'nin inserʉ uya ti'sawʉ yawon i'kwamʉ'pʉ kakʉi'. Eke main uyee'pʉ apono' winɨpai Papa ena' use'man nɨto' iwʉ' tapai, “Iu'ma'sa' man!” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 18 Kamiri' e'weuweuma esi'pʉ, ta'merunsen esi'pʉ, ɨsɨ pe korʉme e'toi'pɨtʉ esi'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsɨ rɨ tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ esi'pʉ. Mɨrɨ waraino tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ esa' pʉra iyesi, ka'pon ekoneka'pʉ si'kɨrɨ, serɨ tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ esi'pʉ ɨsɨ pe tanporon entai.\x - \xo 16:18 \xt Isenpoikasa' 8:5; 11:13, 19\x* 
\v 19 Eke pata e'mopɨtʉ'pʉ osorʉwau iye'to' airɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉpataron kon pata'se' ton uta'morʉka'pʉ. Papa uya eke Paperan kupʉ'pʉ tenu yau, mɨrɨpan uya tʉyuku ensito' pe tʉkokʉ yai ikupʉ'pʉ, kota'man nɨto' tʉuya euku.\x - \xo 16:19 \xt Aisaya 51:17\x* 
\v 20 Tanporon nɨ opa'wʉ amʉ' pʉra iyena'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wʉ' amʉ' pʉra iyena'pʉ.\x - \xo 16:20 \xt Isenpoikasa' 6:14\x* 
\v 21 Eke ton tuna tɨ'mooi 100 pon kaisaro' nan uta'pokʉ'pʉ ka' winɨpai ka'pon amʉ' pona. Mɨrɨ pɨ', ka'pon amʉ' uya Papa pa'nʉkʉ'pʉ, apʉne pʉra ɨsɨ pe kuru mɨrɨ paran esi pɨ'.\x - \xo 16:21 \xt E'sotas 9:23; Isenpoikasa' 11:19\x* 
\c 17  
\s1 Eke Tekumasen 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ a'tai, 7 pan kon inserʉ amʉ' tonpa 7 kaisaron pʉsau amʉ' esa' pe iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ uyee'pʉ upiya', mɨrɨpan uya, “Ɨsi'kɨ, ɨpɨ' ekamato' pe uya eke tekumasen ekota'mato' eseru, kʉrɨ rɨ tu'kan tuna pʉro'po te'sen.\x - \xo 17:1 \xt Iseremaya 51:13\x* 
\v 2 Kin amʉ' non pon kon ekumasa' kʉrɨ rɨ eke tekumasen a'kɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka'pon amʉ' e'taripasa' ɨri inkupʉnʉ euku pɨ',” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 17:2 \xt Aisaya 23:17; Iseremaya 51:7\x* 
\p  
\v 3 Mɨrɨ a'tai, inserʉ uya uyarɨ'pʉ Ita'kwarʉ yau rɨmono' ta'. Mɨrɨ yau, uri'san ene'pʉ uya, isuweyu ene po iyereutasa', Papa sapemato' ese' ton e'menukapɨ'sa' ke iwontɨsa'. 7 kaisa rɨ i'pai ton esi'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 10 kaisa rɨ iretʉ ton.\x - \xo 17:3 \xt Isenpoikasa' 13:1\x* 
\v 4 Uri'san epontɨsa' esi'pʉ tʉtariren pon ya', isuweyu ya', mɨrɨpan uta'kʉ'tɨsa' esi'pʉ korʉ ke, epe'kena' ton tɨ' ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ ton mokon ke. Tenau ko' korʉ pun konekasa' a'sisa' iya esi'pʉ, ɨri ton kuru nuirapanin nan ke iyepe'tɨsa' esi'pʉ, tekumai' ɨri ton ku'sa' iya moron nʉ'pʉ.\x - \xo 17:4 \xt Iseremaya 51:7\x* 
\v 5 Serɨ ese' menukasa' esi'pʉ ipee'pɨ pɨ' i'tu pokena' pen ekamanin pe: 
\pc \sc eke paperan\sc* 
\pc \sc tanporon kon tekumasan\sc* 
\pc \sc mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨri ton kuru rɨ nuirapanin nan non pon kon san.\sc* 
\p  
\v 6 Iye'taripasa' pe uri'san ene'pʉ uya Papa munkɨ amʉ' mʉnʉ ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro Sises ekamanin nan mʉnʉ ke. 
\p Ene uya a'tai, ipan pe rɨ usewansiuka'pʉ.  
\v 7 “Ɨ'rɨ pɨ' ɨusewansiuka?” ta'pʉ inserʉ uya upɨ'. “Ekama uya mɨrɨ ɨpɨ' ɨ'rɨ ekamanin pe uri'san esi mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ene anin pe na'ne', ene 7 kaisaron i'pai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 10 kaisaron iretʉ.  
\v 8 Ene ɨnene'pʉ, iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ, ipʉra na'ne', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuye'ton iya'mu pʉn iteuta\f + \fr 17:8 \fq iya'mu pʉn iteuta - Apis; \ft pata non a'mu yawon, ɨri a'kwarʉ ton a'sito' ya' to' kota'mato' u'matʉ pʉ'kʉ pona.\f* yapai, mɨrɨpan utɨto' oton tʉuma'tato' ya'. Ka'pon amʉ' non po tʉuko'mansan, itese' iye'menukasa' kon pen non ekoneka rawɨrɨ tʉuko'mansan karetaai pɨ' usewansiukato' oton ene, ene tʉuya'nokon a'tai, apʉne pʉra iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ, ipʉra na'ne', e'tane tʉuye'ton.\x - \xo 17:8 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:7; Isenpoikasa' 11:7; Eren 69:28\x* 
\p  
\v 9 “Serɨ esi serɨ pu'kena' pe kuru usenuminkan i'se. 7 kaisa rɨ i'pai na'ne' esi 7 kaisaron wʉ' amʉ', uri'san ereutasa' na'ne' ipo.  
\v 10 Kamoro kanan esi 7 pan kon kin amʉ'. 5 kaisa rɨ to' uta'mo'ka'pʉ, tikin nan esi moro tʉron nɨ uye'sa' pʉra rɨ marɨ iyesi; iye'sa' pe iyesi a'tai, mara rɨ mɨrɨ yau iye'to' oton.  
\v 11 Kʉrɨ rɨ ene moro iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ, e'tane ima'tasa' rʉ'pʉ esi mɨrɨ 8 pe kin amʉ' ku'nin pe, mɨrɨpan esi wapiyaro' 7 pan kon tonpa, mɨrɨpan utɨto' oton ama'tase'na. 
\p  
\v 12 “10 kaisaron iretʉ amʉ' meneine' nan esi 10 pan kon kin amʉ', apʉne rɨ itepuru pe to' enasa' pʉra rɨ marɨ iyesi. E'tane kin pe to' e'to' oton tikin ite'kwa kʉra' emiya era'tɨto' airɨ rɨken ene pokon pe.\x - \xo 17:12 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:24\x* 
\v 13 Pʉsamoro 10 pan kon kin amʉ' esi'pʉ tikin nɨ iteseru, mɨrɨpan kon uya tʉpana'pano kon tʉto' oton ene ena'.  
\v 14 Mɨrɨpan kon usewa'nomato' oton karimeru mʉre pokon pe, e'tane karimeru mʉre enato' oton to' entai, apʉne pʉra itepuru ton epuru pe iyesi, kin amʉ' epuru pe rɨ. Ipokon pe inkɨ'ma'san, inanʉmʉ'san, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipɨkɨron kon iyawɨrɨ te'san e'to' oton,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 15 Inserʉ uya ta'pʉ upɨ', “Tuna amʉ' meneine' tekumasen ereutasa' ipo esi mɨrɨ ka'pon amʉ', tʉron kon rʉko' amʉ', tʉpataron kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉmaimuron kon.  
\v 16 10 kaisaron iretʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ene meneine' uya tekumasen ewaruma'tɨto' oton, tanporo itiwano' mo'kato' oton to' uya, ipon pʉra to' uya iku'to' oton. To' uya anto' oton, mɨrɨpan ma'tanʉ'to' oton to' uya apo' ke.  
\v 17 Apʉne pʉra Papa uya to' ewan ya' ipata'tɨsa' pɨ' ɨ'rɨ rɨ i'se te'to' ku'to' pe to' uya, ɨsi'kaisa rɨ tekonekai' tʉpana'pano kon tʉto' pe to' uya ene ena', ikoneka pe itesa' pe iye'to' pe, Papa maimu uta'ku'tɨ pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ.  
\v 18 Uri'san meneine' esi eke pata, non po te'san kin amʉ' esa',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 18  
\s1 Paperan Uta'mo'kasa' 
\p  
\v 1 Serɨ e'kupʉ'pʉ tʉpo, tʉron nɨ inserʉ uyepʉ ene'pʉ uya Epʉn winɨpai. Eke pe te'to' tʉmeruntɨrʉ yau iyesi'pʉ, mɨrɨpan a'kwarii uya tanporo non a'kwaka'pʉ.  
\v 2 Mɨrɨpan ukɨ'pɨ'nʉmʉ'pʉ eke pe: 
\q1 “Ita'mo'kasa' man! Eke Paperan uta'mo'kasa'! 
\q2 Mɨrɨpan enasa' makoi amʉ' pata'se' pe, 
\q1 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi\f + \fr 18:2 \fq makoi, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq ɨri, \ft Kiri' maimu yau.\f* a'kwarʉ amʉ', 
\q2 ɨri ton, i'se e'nɨto' kon pen nɨ toron amʉ' pata'se' pe iyenasa'.\f + \fr 18:2 \fq Ɨri ton, i'se e'nɨto' kon pen nɨ toron amʉ' pata'se' pe iyenasa'; \ft tʉron nɨ inmenukasa' uya, \fq ɨri ton toron amʉ' pata pe, ɨri rɨ pata pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tewaruma'tɨsen ene pata pe iyenasa', \ft ta KJV uya.\f*\x - \xo 18:2 \xt Aisaya 13:21; 21:9; Iseremaya 50:39; 51:8; Isenpoikasa' 14:8\x* 
\q1  
\v 3 Apʉne pʉra tanporon kon tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' uya 
\q2 waain ensi'pʉ, mɨrɨ ɨsɨ waain iyekumato' euku. 
\q1 Tanporon kon kin amʉ' non pon kon ekumasa' iya'kɨrɨ, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' te'san enasa' ipʉrataaikena' pe, wakʉ ton kuru itapuruui ton tonpa ke rɨ,”\x - \xo 18:3 \xt Aisaya 23:17; Iseremaya 51:7\x* 
\m tukai'. 
\p  
\v 4 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉron nɨ main eta'pʉ uya Epʉn winɨpai se kasa tawon: 
\q1 “Iyapai epa'katɨ', umunkɨ amʉ'! 
\q2 imakooi yau ɨwesi kon namai', itonpa pe tenai', 
\q2 iteparan ton eporo auya'nokon namai'.\x - \xo 18:4 \xt Aisaya 48:20; Iseremaya 50:8; 51:6, 45\x* 
\q1  
\v 5 Apʉne pʉra imakooi uka'putasa' man ka' tepose,\x - \xo 18:5 \xt Iseneses 18:20-21; Iseremaya 51:9\x* 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa uya ɨri ton iteseru kupʉ tenu yau. 
\q1  
\v 6 Ɨpɨ' inkupʉ'pʉ rɨ marɨ iku'kɨ ipɨ',\x - \xo 18:6 \xt Eren 137:8; Iseremaya 50:29\x* 
\q2 asa' ite'kwa iye'to' airɨ ɨpɨ' inkupʉ'pʉ iku'kɨ ipɨ'. 
\q2 I'sawʉ ipe'tɨkɨ ɨuku pe inkoneka'pʉ kata'pano entai asa' ite'kwa ikata'pano e'to' airɨ. 
\q1  
\v 7 E'ne' moronkato' pe iya iku'kɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ isewankamato' pe, 
\q2 eke pe iyesi'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe iyesi'pʉ kasa. 
\q1 Tewan yau mɨ pe iye'kupʉ'pʉ, 
\q2 ‘Moro ereutasa' kwin pe; itaan'pʉ ima'tasa' rʉ'pʉ pe esi pen, 
\q2 tʉuta'kwarʉkai' ukaranto' oton pen,’ ta iya. 
\q1  
\v 8 Mɨrɨ kasa iyesi ke, paran uya iwɨto' oton tikin nan wʉi yau: 
\q2 uma'tan nɨto', tʉuta'kwarʉkai' ukaran nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iwankan, 
\q1 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ apo' uya ipo'tɨto' oton, 
\q2 apʉne pʉra Itepuru Papa iteseru aimenkanin esi meruntɨ pe,”\x - \xo 18:8 \xt Aisaya 47:7-9\x* 
\m tawon. 
\p  
\v 9 “Kin amʉ' non pon kon ɨri pe iya'kɨrɨ iyekumasa' kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iya'kɨrɨ iye'sa' kon wakʉ ton kuru rɨ itapuruui ton pɨkɨrɨ ukaranto' oton tʉuta'kwarʉkai', to' ukaranto' oton ipan pe pata wenai iyepo'tɨ kɨrɨsin ene tʉuya'nokon a'tai.  
\v 10 Ɨnnɨ ipiyapai to' e'to' oton, apʉne pʉra e'ne' moronka iya pɨ', mɨrɨpan kon uya ta: 
\q1 “‘Ɨsɨ kusa! Ɨsɨ kusa, 
\q2 serɨ eke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pana'pan pata Paperan! 
\q1 Inke pʉra rɨ ɨyekota'mato' e'seposa' man!’ 
\m tato' oton.\x - \xo 18:10 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 26:16-17\x* 
\p  
\v 11 “Kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' te'san non pon kon ukaranto' oton iwenai tʉuta'kwarʉkai', apʉne pʉra timamin kon ennanin pʉra iyesi pɨ' mɨrɨ enta'—  
\v 12 to' korʉʉi, to' sirʉpaai, epe'kena' to' tɨpu mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mokon pun; epe'kena' pon renen tato' atʉ ton, tʉtariren pon atʉ, sirʉ', isuweyu pon atʉ, tu'kan nɨ a'po'nan paranka amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aipori tato' winɨpai ikonekasa' ton, epe'kena' ton yʉi winɨpai, karukuri winɨpai, wa'ka pun winɨpai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mapʉrʉ winɨpai;  
\v 13 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ senaman, kiyari isu, karapa, mɨrʉ tato' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'po'nan tʉkɨrɨi'nʉnpasen, waain, are' kasi', wakʉ kuru pʉrowa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wi'; paka amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru amʉ'; kaware amʉ', tararan amʉ'; apiyo' ton ennanin pʉra iyesi pɨ'.\x - \xo 18:13 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 27:12-13, 22\x* 
\p  
\v 14 “Kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' te'san uya se kasa tato' oton ipɨ', ‘Tanporo wakʉ ton i'se ɨwe'sa' rʉ'pʉ utɨ'pʉ man, tanporo ɨimamin ton, wakʉ pe ɨwe'to' utɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ epoto' auya oton pen nɨ.’  
\v 15 Kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' te'san ipʉrataaikena' pe iyenasa' kon mɨrɨ pata yau, e'mʉ'sa'kato' oton ɨnnɨ ipiyapai, apʉne pʉra to' enari'nʉmʉ e'ne' moronka iya pɨ'.\x - \xo 18:15 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 27:31, 36\x* To' ukaranto' oton tʉuta'kwarʉkai', to' ukaranto' oton ipan pe,  
\v 16 mɨrɨpan kon ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ'to' oton: 
\q1 “‘Ɨsɨ kusa! Ɨsɨ kusa mɨrɨ eke pata, 
\q2 tepontɨsen pe iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ epe'kena' pon renen tato' ya', tʉtariren mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ isuweyu pon ya', 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iye'wontɨpɨ'sa' rʉ'pʉ korʉ konekasa' a'kʉ pe ke, epe'kena' ton tɨ' ke, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mokon ke! 
\q1  
\v 17 Tikin ite'kwa kʉra' emiya era'tɨto' a'tai rɨ eke kuru itimamin uma'ta'pʉ!’\x - \xo 18:17 \xt Aisaya 23:14; Isi'kiyerʉ 27:26-30\x* 
\p “Tanporo eke kanau anin pe te'san, kanau yau tʉutɨsan, yau te'tʉrawasomasan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉron kon nɨ parau kau te'tʉrawasomasan e'mʉ'sa'kato' oton ɨnnɨ.  
\v 18 Mɨrɨpan kon ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnto' oton iyepo'tɨ kɨrɨsin ene tʉuya'nokon a'tai, ‘Moro rɨ pe' pata ne'tai serɨ eke pata warai?’ tato' oton to' uya.\x - \xo 18:18 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 27:32\x* 
\v 19 Amuru tʉrʉ'pɨ'to' oton to' uya ti'pai kon pona, tʉuta'kwarʉkai' akaramʉi'ma to' ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ'to' oton: 
\q1 “‘Ɨsɨ kusa! Ɨsɨ kusa mɨrɨ eke pata! 
\q2 Mɨrɨ pata winɨ kamoro parau kau kanau esanon 
\q2 ena'pʉ imaminkena' pe, itimamin winɨ rɨ. 
\q1 Tikin ite'kwa kʉra' emiya era'tɨto' airɨ ima'tasa'!\x - \xo 18:19 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 27:30-34\x* 
\q1  
\v 20 Oso sɨ! Epʉn, pori' pe e'kɨ, apʉne pʉra ima'tasa' pɨ'. 
\q2 Pori' pe e'tɨ', Papa munkɨ amʉ', itekare ekamai' enno'sa' kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pu'kena' ton, 
\q1 apʉne pʉra Papa uya ɨpɨ'nokon inkupʉ'pʉ ku'sa' mɨrɨ ipɨ',’” 
\m tato' oton.\x - \xo 18:20 \xt Isu'taronomi 32:43; Iseremaya 51:48\x* 
\p  
\v 21 Mɨrɨ a'tai, meruntɨ inserʉ uya tɨ' anʉmʉ'pʉ eke a'nai' e'pato' yai kaisaron nɨ, mɨrɨpan eno'ma'pʉ iya parau ka' se kasa tai'ma: 
\q1 “Serɨ kasa ɨsɨ pe 
\q2 eke pata Paperan eno'mato' oton, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ epoton pe pʉra rɨ kanan.\x - \xo 18:21 \xt Iseremaya 51:63-64; Isi'kiyerʉ 26:21\x* 
\q1  
\v 22 Wai, a'pu turunpanin nan, wai, sarakuwa turunpanin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wai tʉronpi' turunpanin nan 
\q2 usetato' oton pen nɨ kanan ayau. 
\q1 Ti'tui' pʉra rɨ ɨ'rɨ rɨ tʉka'pɨ'se te'tʉrawasomasan 
\q2 e'sepoto' oton kanan pen ayau, 
\q1 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'nai' e'pato' yai 
\q2 usetato' oton pen nɨ kanan ayau.\x - \xo 18:22 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 26:13; Aisaya 24:8\x* 
\q1  
\v 23 Raan'pu uya pata wei'tɨsa' usento' oton pen nɨ kanan ayau, 
\q1 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ temari'masen uri'san mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itaan'pʉ maimu 
\q2 usetato' oton pen nɨ kanan ayau. 
\q1 Ɨpoitorʉ ton kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' te'san esi'pʉ eke ton kuru rɨ serɨ yau 
\q2 mɨrɨpan enwoke' pe ɨwe'to' ke tanporo tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' ano'ma'pʉ auya.\x - \xo 18:23 \xt Iseremaya 7:34; 25:10\x* 
\q1  
\v 24 Paperan po pu'kena' amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ ton, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo non po iwɨsa' kon mʉnʉ e'seporo'pʉ,”\x - \xo 18:24 \xt Iseremaya 51:49\x* 
\m ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 19  
\s1 Areruya! 
\p  
\v 1 Serɨ e'ma'pʉ pe, eke anpisin ka'pon amʉ' maimu waraino eta'pʉ uya Epʉn po, se kasa tawon: 
\q1 “Areruya! 
\q1 Epika'tɨn nɨto', eke pe iku'to' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ meruntɨ esi Papa iwano' pe, 
\q2  
\v 2 i'napai rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe kuru eseru aimenkanin pe iyesi. 
\q1 Eke tekumasen eno'masa' iya, 
\q2 non ano'ma pɨ' iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ ɨri teseru ke. 
\q1 Papa uya ikota'masa' tʉpoitorʉ ton mʉnʉ epe'pʉ pe,” 
\m ta'pʉ to' uya.\x - \xo 19:2 \xt Isu'taronomi 32:43; 2 Kin Amʉ' 9:7\x* 
\v 3 To' ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ'kaa'pʉ kanan, 
\q1 “Areruya! 
\q1 Iyepo'tɨ kɨrɨsin ekainʉmʉ inke rɨ,” 
\m tukai'.\x - \xo 19:3 \xt Aisaya 34:10\x* 
\p  
\v 4 24 kaisaron kon itepuru ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asakɨrɨ'nan kon ene amʉ' uta'mo'ka'pʉ Papa apurɨpɨtʉ pe, apono' po iyereutasa', mɨrɨpan kon ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ: 
\q1 “Amen! Areruya!” 
\m tukai'. 
\s1 Karimeru Mʉre Emari'ma Uta're'tɨ 
\p  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ a'tai, main useta'pʉ apono' winɨpai, se kasa tawon: 
\q1 “Papa, itese' pɨ' e'nɨto' apurɨpɨ'tɨ' 
\q2 tanporon kon ipoitorʉ ton, 
\q1 ɨmɨrɨ'nokon inamanin nan, 
\q2 aiko ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke ton!”\x - \xo 19:5 \xt Eren 115:13\x* 
\m tawon. 
\p  
\v 6 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, eta'pʉ uya anpisin ka'pon amʉ' maimu waraino, eke tuna ena maimu waraino, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pe korʉme e'tʉrʉnpɨtʉ waraino. Se kasa tato' uya eta'pʉ uya, 
\q1 “Papa apurɨpɨ'tɨ'! 
\q2 Apʉne pʉra Itepuru Papa Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye' esi kin pe pɨ'.\x - \xo 19:6 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 1:24; Eren 93:1; 97:1; 99:1\x* 
\q1  
\v 7 Epori'manpai'nokon, pori' pe e'nɨpai'nokon, 
\q2 eke pe iye'to' apurɨpɨ'pai'nokon! 
\q1 Karimeru mʉre emari'ma weyu e'seposa' man, 
\q2 ino'pʉ pe te'ton ekonekasa' man ite'ma ta'. 
\q1  
\v 8 Epe'kena' pon renen tato', enkena' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itoi'masa' pen ke 
\q2 irepasa' iyepontɨto' ya' pe,” 
\m tukai'. (Epe'kena' pon renen tato' esi ipokena' pe wakʉ ton nʉkupʉ'pʉ rʉ'pʉ.) 
\p  
\v 9 Mɨrɨ a'tai, inserʉ uya ta'pʉ upɨ', “Serɨ imenuka': ‘Pori' pe kuru kamoro esi mɨrɨ karimeru mʉre emari'ma uta're'tɨ ya' ikɨ'masa' kon!’” Miyarɨ rɨ inserʉ uya, “I'napairon kuru rɨ serɨ Papa Maimu,” ta'pʉ.\x - \xo 19:9 \xt Ma'siu 22:2-3\x* 
\p  
\v 10 Uta'mo'ka'pʉ i'ta piyau apurɨpɨ'se'na, e'tane, “Kʉ'kupʉi. Awaraino rɨ marɨ urɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨtonpa ton na'ne' warai rɨ marɨ i'napairon Sises nenpoika'pʉ pokon nɨ marɨ. Papa apurɨpɨ'kɨ! I'napairon Sises nenpoikanʉ uya ka'pon amʉ' koneka tʉusauro'san pe pu'kena' amʉ' kasa,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Aimu'nan Kaware Pon 
\p  
\v 11 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, Epʉn uta'koka ene'pʉ uya, aimu'nan kaware esi'pʉ, ipo te'sen ese' esi'pʉ Iyawɨron Kuru, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ I'napairon. Wakʉ pe ɨsi'kaisa rɨ eseru aimenkanin mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉusewa'nomasen.\x - \xo 19:11 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 1:1; Eren 96:13; Aisaya 11:4\x* 
\v 12 Itenu ton esi'pʉ apo' epo'tɨ kasa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tu'kan nɨ aro', kʉron amʉ' esi'pʉ i'pai po. Ese' e'menukasa' esi'pʉ ipɨ', ɨnʉ' ni'tunʉ pen nɨ, kʉrɨ rɨ uya rɨken i'tu.\x - \xo 19:12 \xt Taniyerʉ 10:6\x* 
\v 13 Ipon, iyau iye'to' esi'pʉ mʉn ka' iki'sa' pe. Itese' esa'to' yau esi “Papa Maimu” tukai'.  
\v 14 Epʉn pon kon soisa amʉ' utɨ esi'pʉ ipɨkɨrɨ, aimu'na' nan kaware amʉ' po'ne, aimu'nan, itoi'masa' pen epe'kena' pon renen tato' ya' tepontɨpɨ'se.  
\v 15 Iyɨkena' supara epa'ka'pʉ inta yai, mɨrɨ ke tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' wɨto' iya oton. “To' esa' pe iye'to' oton wa'ka pun itɨɨi pe,”\f + \fr 19:15 \ft Eren 2:9\f* mɨrɨpan uya waain kasu'kato' oton, Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye' Papa uya kota'man nɨto' kasu'kato' en yai.\x - \xo 19:15 \xt Aisaya 63:3; Isowerʉ 3:13; Isenpoikasa' 14:20\x* 
\v 16 Ipon pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ite'mata pɨ' ese' e'menukasa' esi'pʉ: 
\pc Kin amʉ' epuru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itepuru ton epuru 
\m tukai'. 
\p  
\v 17 Mɨrɨ a'tai, inserʉ e'mʉ'sa'kasa' ene'pʉ uya wʉi enu yau. Eke pe ikɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ tanporo kau te'san toron amʉ' uya etato' pe, “Ɨsi'tɨ', tanporo eke pe Papa uta're'tɨ ya' amʉratɨ'.  
\v 18 Ɨsi'tɨ', kin amʉ' pun, soisa amʉ' epuru ton pun, meruntɨ ton pun, kaware amʉ' pun, to' po te'san pun, tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' poitorʉ pe te'san mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' enawon kon pen, eke ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aiko ton nɨ nɨrɨ pun anɨ kon pa,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 19:18 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 39:17-20\x* 
\p  
\v 19 Mɨrɨ a'tai, ene, kin amʉ' non pon kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' soisaai amʉ' amʉrasa' ene'pʉ uya, kaware pon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ isoisaai amʉ' ewa'nomase'na.  
\v 20 E'tane ene a'si'pʉ to' uya pariki'si ta', ennakanin pu'kena' pokon pe, eke itʉrawasooi ton, i'tuto' ipɨ' ku'nin nʉ'pʉ ipiyau. Serɨ i'tuto' ipɨ' ton ke kamoro ene ma'kʉʉi ke iye'menukasa' kon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipe ika'sa' apurɨpɨ'nin nʉ'san enku'tɨ'pʉ iya mɨrɨ. Ene mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ennakanin pu'kena' eno'ma'pʉ to' uya nurɨne apo' ku'pɨri ka' sorʉ'pa ke tepo'tɨsen.\x - \xo 19:20 \xt Isenpoikasa' 13:1-18\x* 
\v 21 To' soisaai amʉ' wɨnɨ'pʉ supara kaware pon mʉta yapai tepa'kasen uya, mɨrɨpan tanporon kon toron amʉ' uya i'se te'to' kon pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ to' pun anɨ'pʉ. 
\c 20  
\s1 1,000 Kaisaro' Nan Wʉipiya Ton 
\p  
\v 1 Inserʉ u'tɨ ene'pʉ uya Epʉn yapai, iya'mu pʉn iteuta\f + \fr 20:1 \fq iya'mu pʉn iteuta; \ft Apis—pata non a'mu yawon, ɨri a'kwarʉ ton a'sito' ya' to' kota'mato' u'matʉ pʉ'kʉ pona.\f* kii mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke i'sen itenau.  
\v 2 Urupere a'si'pʉ iya, kʉrɨ rɨ esi penaro' rɨ ɨkʉi, Makoi, mɨrɨ pe pʉra Se'tan,\f + \fr 20:2 \fq Se'tan \ft - Makoi ese' isakon, \fq Papa eseru ewaruma'tɨnin \ft ta e'kwa pe; v. 6-8 nɨrɨ.\f* mɨrɨpan auronpɨtʉ'pʉ iya 1,000 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya iye'to' pe.\x - \xo 20:2 \xt Iseneses 3:1\x* 
\v 3 Inserʉ uya eno'ma'pʉ iya'mu pʉn iteuta ya'. A'koro'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan a'sikʉ'pʉ iya, tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' enku'tɨ iya namai' 1,000 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya u'matʉ pona rɨ. Mɨrɨ tʉpo, inonkato' pe aka'ne' pe rɨ. 
\p  
\v 4 Mɨrɨ a'tai, apono' amʉ' ene'pʉ uya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipo'ne iyereutapɨ'sa' kon kamoro eke pe to' e'to' pe eseru aimenkanin nan pe irepasa' kon. I'mʉrʉpɨ'sa' kon a'kwarʉ kanan ene'pʉ uya i'napairon Sises nenpoika'pʉ ekama to' uya pɨkɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa Maimu pɨkɨrɨ. Ene apurɨpɨ'sa' to' uya pʉra iyesi, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipe ika'sa' ene ma'kʉʉi eposa' to' uya pʉra iyesi tʉpee'pɨ kon pɨ', mɨrɨ pe pʉra temiyatʉ kon pɨ'. Mɨrɨpan kon e'mʉ'sa'kasa' terikʉ kon tʉpo esi'pʉ kin pe Kʉrai pokon pe 1,000 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya.\x - \xo 20:4 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:9, 22\x* 
\v 5 (Tʉron kon iyeri'pɨ'sa' kon amʉ' e'mʉ'sa'ka pʉra iyesi'pʉ 1,000 kaisaron wʉipiya u'matʉ pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ.) Serɨ esi wapiyaro' iyeri'pɨ'sa' kon e'mʉ'sa'kato'.  
\v 6 Pori' pe kuru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe kamoro esi wapiyaro' kon iyeri'sa' kon e'mʉ'sa'ka koro'tau na'ne' nan. Itisakon uma'tan nɨto' pana'pano pʉra iyesi to' entai, e'tane Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan pe to' e'to' oton Papa iwano' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Kʉrai iwano' pe, mɨrɨpan kon e'to' oton itepuru pe ipokon pe 1,000 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya. 
\s1 Se'tan Ma'tanʉkʉ 
\p  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ 1,000 kaisaron wʉipiya ton u'ma'sa' a'tai, Se'tan e'nonkato' oton pariki'si tapai,  
\v 8 mɨrɨpan utɨto' oton tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' Kokʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Makokʉ amʉ' enku'tɨse'na—asakɨrɨ'nan non ekun yawon kon. To' amʉranʉ'to' iya oton ɨsewa'nomase'na, anpisin pe parau e'pi pon wɨ'sɨ' esi kasa.\x - \xo 20:8 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 7:2; 38:2, 9, 15\x* 
\v 9 To' utanʉnsa' utɨ'pʉ non emʉ' kaisa rɨ e'sorʉ'mai'ma, mɨrɨpan kon uya Papa munkɨ amʉ' pata'se' oimentɨ'pʉ, eke pata\f + \fr 20:9 \fq eke pata; \ft Serɨ esi Surusiran ta e'kwa pe.\f* ini'nʉnkanʉ, e'tane apo' u'tɨ'pʉ Epʉn winɨpai, mɨrɨpan uya to' ma'tanʉkʉ'pʉ.  
\v 10 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, Makoi, to' enku'tɨnin nʉ'pʉ useno'ma'pʉ sorʉ'pa epo'tɨ ku'pɨri ka', ene mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ennakanin pu'kena' eno'makaa'pʉ ika' rʉ'pʉ ka'; mɨrɨpan kon ekota'mato' oton wʉi kaisa rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ewarupɨ kaisa rɨ inke rɨ, inke rɨ. 
\s1 Aimenkan Nɨto' U'ma'sa' 
\p  
\v 11 Mɨrɨ a'tai, eke aimu'nan apono' ene'pʉ uya, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipo te'sen. Non mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka' apʉrʉmʉ'pʉ ipiyapai, to' pata oton pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ.  
\v 12 Iyeri'sa' kon ene'pʉ uya, eke ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aiko ton pokon pe rɨ, to' e'mʉ'sa'kasa' apono' piyau. Kareta amʉ' uta'koka'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉron nɨ kareta uta'koka'pʉ, serɨ esi tʉuko'manton kon karetaai. Iyeri'sa' kon eseru aimenka'pʉ to' uya to' nʉkupʉ'pʉ pɨkɨrɨ, kareta yau iye'menukasa' pɨkɨrɨ.\x - \xo 20:12 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:9-10\x* 
\v 13 Parau uya tʉkau iyeri'pɨ'sa' kon nonka'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eri'nɨto' uya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ orʉ iyeri'pɨ'sa' kon pata'se'\f + \fr 20:13 \fq Etis; \ft Hades, Enkeri'si maimu yau; iyeri'sa' kon nono. (Apʉne Isenpoikasa' 1:18 enkɨ.)\f* uya tʉna'si'pʉ ton nonka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon eseru utaimenka'pʉ to' kaisa rɨ to' nʉkupʉ'pʉ pɨkɨrɨ.  
\v 14 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, eri'nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyeri'sa' kon pata eno'ma'pʉ to' uya apo' ku'pɨri ka'. Serɨ apo' ku'pɨri esi iyakon ite'kwa pe eri'nɨto'.  
\v 15 Ɨnʉ' rɨ itese' e'menukasa' eposa' pʉra iyesi yau uko'man nɨto' karetaai pɨ' eno'ma'pʉ apo' ku'pɨri ka'. 
\c 21  
\s1 Emenna' Epʉn Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Emenna' Non 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ a'tai, emenna' Epʉn mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ emenna' non ene'pʉ uya. Wapiyaro' Epʉn mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wapiyaro' non pʉra iyena'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ parau pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ.\x - \xo 21:1 \xt Aisaya 65:17; 66:22; 2 Pi'ta 3:13\x* 
\v 2 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Wakʉ Pata ene'pʉ uya, emenna' Surusiran u'tɨ Epʉn apai, Papa winɨpai, iyekonekasa' temari'masen uri'san uta'kʉ'tɨsa' ama'non pe kasa tʉtaan'pʉ e'ma ta'.\x - \xo 21:2 \xt Aisaya 52:1; 61:10; Isenpoikasa' 3:12\x* 
\v 3 Eke main usaurokʉ eta'pʉ uya apono' winɨpai, “Serɨ pe si Papa pata'se' man ka'pon amʉ' piyau. To' piyau iko'manto' oton, imunkɨ amʉ' pe to' e'to' oton. Tʉmɨrɨ pe kuru Papa e'to' oton to' piyau, itese' pɨ' to' e'to' e' pe.\x - \xo 21:3 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 37:27; Ripaiti'kas 26:11-12\x* 
\v 4 Tanporo to' enu paru a'munakato' iya oton. Eri'nɨto' pʉra rɨ iye'to' oton, tʉuta'kwarʉkai' ukaran nɨ pʉra rɨ, ukaran nɨ pʉra rɨ, e'ne' pʉra rɨ, penaro' ton pʉra iyesi wenai,” tawon.\x - \xo 21:4 \xt Aisaya 25:8; 35:10; 65:19\x* 
\p  
\v 5 Kʉrɨ rɨ apono' po iyereutasa' uya, “Serɨ pe tanporon konekasa' uya man emenna' pe,” ta'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ upɨ' kanan ta'pʉ iya. “Serɨ imenuka', apʉne pʉra serɨ main ton esi i'napai rɨ kuru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tapurɨsen pe kuru iyesi,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 6 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ, “Iu'ma'sa' si man,” ta'pʉ iya. “Urɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Arʉ'pa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Omeka, Iye'sara'tɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Iu'matʉ. Ɨnʉ' rɨ tuna'kiri' ke na'ne' o'pa uya mɨrɨ te'masen pen nɨ tuna ke, uko'man nɨto' tuna'kwaai ke.\x - \xo 21:6 \xt Aisaya 55:1\x* 
\v 7 Ɨnʉ' rɨ entakanin nʉ'pʉ uya serɨ epoto' oton uwinɨpai, itese' pɨ' iye'to' Papa pe esi mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ umu pe iye'to' oton.\x - \xo 21:7 \xt 2 Sanwerʉ 7:14; Eren 89:26-27\x* 
\v 8 E'tane enari'kena' ton, apurɨnin nan pen, ɨri ku'nin nan, te'wɨsan, tekumasan, enwoke' ton, ika'sa' apurɨnin nan, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo kasi ye' ton—to' pata'se' e'to' oton sorʉ'pa epo'tɨ ku'pɨri. Mɨrɨ esi iyakon ite'kwa pe uma'tan nɨto',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Emenna' Surusiran 
\p  
\v 9 7 kaisaron kon inserʉ amʉ' tonpa, 7 kaisaron pʉsau amʉ' epe'tɨpɨ'sa' esanon nʉ'san iu'matʉ rɨ 7 kaisaron paran ke, uyee'pʉ upiya', mɨrɨpan uya, “Ɨsi'kɨ, uri'san karimeru mʉre nʉmari'manʉ ino'pʉ ekamato' pe uya ɨpɨ',” ta'pʉ iya upɨ'.  
\v 10 Uyarɨ'pʉ iya Ita'kwarʉ yau eke, ka'tawon wʉ' pona, mɨrɨpan uya Surusiran, wakʉ pata uyepʉ Epʉn apai Papa winɨpai ekama'pʉ upɨ'.\x - \xo 21:10 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 40:2\x* 
\v 11 Irentasa' Papa kʉroreei ke, pata urentasa' esi'pʉ epe'kena' kuru tɨ' kasa, tɨ' isaspa tato' kasa, awai'nan tɨ' kʉrestarʉ tato' kasa.  
\v 12 Eke, ka'tawon iwekupiri esi'pʉ, 12 kaisa rɨ imʉra'taai ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 12 kaisa rɨ inserʉ amʉ' esi 12 kaisaron mʉra'ta amʉ' airɨ'ne. Mʉra'ta pɨ'ne 12 kaisaron kon Esuwerʉ pon kon ese' ton e'menukasa' esi'pʉ.  
\v 13 Imʉra'taai amʉ' esi'pʉ osorʉwau'ne, osorʉwau iyesi'pʉ wʉi enu uye'to' winɨ, osorʉwau iyesi'pʉ wʉi enu enuku enwo'netʉ winɨ, osorʉwau iyesi'pʉ wʉi enu enuku kamisi winɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ osorʉwau iyesi'pʉ wʉi enu utɨto' winɨ.\x - \xo 21:13 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 48:30-35\x* 
\v 14 Mɨrɨ pata wekupiri ekonekasa' esi'pʉ 12 kaisaron tɨ', iyapon pe te'sen po'ne, mɨrɨpan pɨ'ne 12 kaisaron kon itekare ekamai' karimeru mʉre nennoko'san ese' ton e'menukasa' esi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 15 Inserʉ, uyauro'kanin nʉ'pʉ enau yʉi korʉ pun konekasa' esi'pʉ pata i'tuto' ike, imʉra'taai ton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iwekupiri ton.\x - \xo 21:15 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 40:3\x* 
\v 16 Pata esi'pʉ ɨsi'kaisa rɨ, ikusano kaisa rɨ ika'ta esi'pʉ. Inserʉ uya pata i'tu'pʉ tʉyɨɨi ke; mɨrɨpan e'seporo'pʉ 12,000 kaisa rɨ yʉi epotorʉ'pʉ pe ikusano,\f + \fr 21:16 \fq 12,000 kaisa rɨ yʉi epotorʉ'pʉ pe ikusano; \ft 12,000 stetiya—1500 e'to' airɨ mayirʉ.\f* ika'ta mɨrɨ kaisarɨ rɨ marɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ikawono esi'pʉ ikusano kaisarɨ rɨ marɨ.  
\v 17 Inserʉ uya iwekupiri i'tu'pʉ, mɨrɨpan e'seporo'pʉ 144 kaisa rɨ ite'kwa yʉi ikawono,\f + \fr 21:17 \fq ikawono; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq iti'simu.\f*\f + \fr 21:17 \fq 144 kaisa rɨ ite'kwa yʉi ikawono; \ft 144 kiyupi' amʉ'—200 e'to' airɨ pi'.\f* mɨrɨ esi'pʉ ka'pon napurɨnʉ airon i'tuto' ike nekamanʉ awɨrɨ.  
\v 18 Iwekupiri esi'pʉ tɨ', isaspa tato' pe; eke pata esi'pʉ korʉ pe, esukenan wanamari kasa.  
\v 19 Pata wekupiri apon a'kʉ'tɨsa' esi'pʉ ɨ'si'tai rɨ epe'kena' ton tɨ' amʉ' ke. Wapiyaro' kuru iyapon esi'pʉ tɨ' isaspa tato', isakon esi'pʉ tɨ' sa'paya tato', itosorʉwano esi'pʉ tɨ' isarʉ'setoni tato',\f + \fr 21:19 \fq Isarʉ'setoni; \ft chalcedony, Enkeri'si pe. Mɨrɨ ton epe'kena' ton tɨ' amʉ' esi mɨrɨ warai'nan mɨrɨ ton tukai' i'tu kuru pʉra.\f* itasakɨrɨ'pano esi'pʉ tɨ' emɨrarʉ tato',  
\v 20 5 pe iku'nin esi'pʉ tɨ' sarʉtone' tato', 6 pe iku'nin esi'pʉ tɨ' kaneriyan tato', 7 pe iku'nin esi'pʉ tɨ' kiri'sorai' tato', 8 pe iku'nin esi'pʉ tɨ' pererʉ tato', 9 pe iku'nin esi'pʉ tɨ' to'pas tato', 10 pe iku'nin esi'pʉ tɨ' kʉrisopʉres tato', 11 pe iku'nin esi'pʉ tɨ' isa'sen tato', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 12 pe iku'nin esi'pʉ tɨ' ama'tes tato'.  
\v 21 12 kaisaron mʉra'ta amʉ' esi'pʉ 12 kaisaron mokon pun amʉ', tikin pa'ne mʉra'ta ekonekasa' esi'pʉ tikin pa'nan mokon pun ke, eke asanta, eke pata e'ma esi'pʉ esukenan korʉ pe, awai'ne wanamari kasa.\x - \xo 21:21 \xt Aisaya 54:11-12\x* 
\p  
\v 22 Use'man nɨto', ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' ene uya pʉra iyesi'pʉ pata yau, apʉne pʉra use'man nɨto', ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' pe rɨ Itepuru Papa Meruntɨ pe kuru te'sen ye' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre esi pɨ'.  
\v 23 Mɨrɨ pata esi wʉi enu i'se pʉra rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra kapʉi tʉwei'tɨnin pe, apʉne pʉra Papa a'kwarii uya rɨ iwei'tɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre esi iraan'puui pe.\x - \xo 21:23 \xt Aisaya 60:19-20\x* 
\v 24 Tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' usato' oton iweyu yau, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kin amʉ' non pon kon uya timamin kon ne'to' oton iya'.\x - \xo 21:24 \xt Aisaya 60:3\x* 
\v 25 Pata mʉra'taai ton amʉ' e'to' oton ta'kokai' rɨ wʉi tase, ita'koto' oton pen nɨ, apʉne pʉra ewarupɨ pʉra iye'to' oton mɨrɨ yau.  
\v 26 Tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' to' e'to' eke pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' imamin ton ne'to' oton mɨrɨ pata ya'.\x - \xo 21:26 \xt Aisaya 60:11\x* 
\v 27 Ɨri pe na'ne' ewonto' oton pen nɨ mɨrɨ pata ya', mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨnʉ' rɨ Papa ewaruma ku'nin, mɨrɨ pe pʉra kasi pe te'sen, e'tane kamo rɨken karimeru mʉre uko'man nɨto' karetaai pɨ' rɨken itese' e'menukasa' kon ewonto' oton iya'.\x - \xo 21:27 \xt Aisaya 52:1; Isi'kiyerʉ 44:9\x* 
\c 22  
\s1 Uko'man Nɨto' Tuna'kwaai 
\p  
\v 1 Inserʉ uya tʉu'tɨsen tuna uko'man nɨto' tuna'kwaai enpoika'pʉ uyena', awai'nan tɨ' kʉrestarʉ tato' warai, Papa apon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre apon winɨpai,\x - \xo 22:1 \xt Isi'kiyerʉ 47:1; Sakaraya 14:8\x* 
\v 2 mɨrɨpan u'tɨ esi'pʉ pata e'ma aporo' poro. Sen winɨ'ne ite'pi po uko'man nɨto' ku'nin ton ye' esi'pʉ, 12 kaisa rɨ ite'kwa tepetasen tikin nan wʉipiya yau, tikin ite'kwa tikin nan kapʉi yau, mɨrɨpan are ton esi tʉpataron kon ka'pon amʉ' epi'tɨto' ike pe.\x - \xo 22:2 \xt Iseneses 2:9; Isi'kiyerʉ 47:12\x* 
\v 3 Ɨ'rɨ rɨ Papa nʉpa'nʉkʉ'pʉ e'to' oton pen nɨ mɨrɨ pata yau. Papa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ karimeru mʉre apon e'to' oton mɨrɨ pata yau, mɨrɨpan poitorʉ ton uya apurɨpɨ'to' oton.\x - \xo 22:3 \xt Sakaraya 14:11\x* 
\v 4 To' uya itemʉ' ento' oton, itese' e'menukasa' e'to' oton to' pee'pɨ pɨ'ne.  
\v 5 Ewarupɨ pʉra rɨ iye'to' oton, raan'pu i'se pʉra rɨ to' e'to' oton mɨrɨ pe pʉra wʉi enu rɨ, apʉne pʉra Itepuru Papa e'to' oton to' weyu pe, mɨrɨpan kon e'to' oton esa' wannɨ, kin amʉ' pe inke rɨ, inke rɨ.\x - \xo 22:5 \xt Aisaya 60:19; Taniyerʉ 7:18\x* 
\v 6 Inserʉ uya ta'pʉ upɨ', “Serɨ main esi i'napai rɨ kuru, tapurɨsen pe kuru iyesi. Itepuru Papa ta'kwarʉ tʉnin pu'kena' amʉ' ena' uya, inserʉ enno'sa', serɨ pe kuru te'ku'ton ekamase'na tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨ',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Sises Uye'nɨ Pɨ' Man 
\p  
\v 7 “Etakɨ,” ta pɨ' Sises man, “Serɨ pe kuru uye'ai'! Pori' pe kuru kamoro esi mɨrɨ serɨ kareta yau isekamasa' apurɨnin nan,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 8 Urɨ, Isaan uya serɨ ton eta'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ene'pʉ. Etasa' uya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ensa' uya a'tai, uta'mo'ka'pʉ inserʉ, uyenu ya' enpoikanin nʉ'pʉ pʉta piyau apurɨpɨ'se'na.  
\v 9 E'tane, “Kʉ'kupʉi,” ta'pʉ iya upɨ', “Awaraino rɨ marɨ urɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨtonpa ton pu'kena' amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro serɨ kareta yau iye'menukasa' awɨron kon tonpa. Papa apurɨpɨ'kɨ!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 10 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ upɨ' ta'pʉ iya, “Ama' pe, te'ku'ton ekamanin, serɨ kareta yawon kʉsenkurunpai, apʉne pʉra a'ko pe tanporo iye'ku'to' weyu man.  
\v 11 Kʉrɨ ɨri ku'nin nesii ɨri kupʉ pɨ' rɨ; kʉrɨ ɨri pe na'ne' nesii ɨri pe rɨ; kʉrɨ ipokena' ku'nin nesii ikupʉ pɨ' rɨ; kʉrɨ wakʉ pe na'ne' nesii wakʉ pe rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 22:11 \xt Taniyerʉ 12:10\x* 
\p  
\v 12 “Etakɨ,” ta Sises uya, “Serɨ pe kuru uye'ai'. To' epe'pʉ ton sine'ai' uya'kɨrɨ tikin pa'ne to' repato' pe uya, to' nʉkupʉ'pʉ pɨkɨrɨ rɨ.\x - \xo 22:12 \xt Aisaya 40:10; 62:11; Eren 28:4; Iseremaya 17:10\x* 
\v 13 Urɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Arʉ'pa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Omeka; Wapiyaro', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Iu'matʉ; Iyepiya'tɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Iu'matʉ.\x - \xo 22:13 \xt Isenpoikasa' 1:8, 17; 2:8; Aisaya 44:6; 48:12\x* 
\p  
\v 14 “Pori' pe kuru kamoro esi tʉpon kon korʉkasa' to' uya na'ne' wakʉ pe, mɨrɨpan kon repato' oton Papa uya uko'man nɨto' ku'nin ye' eperu ke, to' ewonto' pe mʉra'ta amʉ' awɨrɨ eke pata ya'.\x - \xo 22:14 \xt Iseneses 2:9; 3:22\x* 
\v 15 Eke pata pʉrorooi po pero amʉ'; enwoke' eseru ku'nin nan, ekumanpɨ' te'san, te'wɨsan, ika'sa' apurɨnin nan, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kasi ye' ton, main ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉku'se esi. 
\p  
\v 16 “Urɨ, Sises uya uinserʉʉi enno'sa' ɨpiya'nokon so'si amʉ' auro'kanin pe. Urɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Tepi' Atʉ rʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Ipa rʉ'pʉ, a'kwa, pata emakʉ a'taino Kaiyono',” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 22:16 \xt Aisaya 11:1, 10\x* 
\p  
\v 17 Iya'kwarʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inmari'manʉ uri'san uya, “Ɨsi'kɨ!” ta, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' rɨ serɨ etayai'ne', “Ɨsi'kɨ!” nɨkai rɨ marɨ. Tɨwɨ tuna'kiri' ke na'ne' nʉyepʉi, tɨwɨ i'se na'ne' te'masen pen uko'man nɨto' tuna'kwaai anʉmʉi.\x - \xo 22:17 \xt Aisaya 55:1\x* 
\p  
\v 18 Tanporon kon serɨ kareta yawon te'ku'ton ekamanin maimu etanin nan panama uya: Ɨnʉ' rɨ itonpa'tɨpɨ'nin nʉ'pʉ esi yau, Papa uya rɨ kanan paran tonpa'tɨto' oton serɨ kareta yau isekamasa' na'ne'.  
\v 19 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' rɨ serɨ pu'kena' pe ekamanin kareta yapai imo'kanin esi yau, Papa uya rɨ ineporonʉ uko'man nɨto' e' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ eke pata yau isekamasa' na'ne' serɨ kareta yau mo'ka mɨrɨ ipiyapai.\x - \xo 22:19 \xt Isu'taronomi 4:2; 12:32\x* 
\p  
\v 20 Tanporo serɨ ton ekamanin nʉ'pʉ uya, “I'napai rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ; serɨ pe kuru uye'ai',” ta. 
\p Amen. Ɨsi'kɨ, Itepuru Sises. 
\p  
\v 21 Wakʉ nonkasa' Itepuru Sises uya nesii Papa munkɨ amʉ'\f + \fr 22:21 \fq Papa munkɨ amʉ'; \ft tʉron nɨ imenukasa' yau, \fq tanporon nɨ, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq tanporon nɨ Papa munkɨ amʉ'\f* piyau. Amen.